Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.55,0:00:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to another edition \Nof JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.09,0:00:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are this month’s highlights: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.29,0:00:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it like to engage \Nin the special metropolitan witnessing work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the bustling United States city \Nof San Francisco? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.46,0:00:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll hear encouraging experiences \Nfrom brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,who preach \Nin this diverse language field.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can young ones \Nserve Jehovah successfully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.34,0:00:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,even if their family’s \Nspiritual activity stops? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.34,0:00:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll hear from a sister who tells \Nwhat kept her love for Jehovah growing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.31,0:00:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout her family’s \Nbusy show business career.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.85,0:00:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In our Preparing for Marriage series, \Nwe’ll learn how those who are dating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.22,0:00:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,can get to know \N“the secret person of the heart” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.09,0:00:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,before making \Na solemn lifelong commitment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.86,0:00:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll discuss \Nthe beautiful quality of loyalty, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.07,0:00:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,including an interview with a couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.37,0:00:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who has served Jehovah loyally \Nfor over 60 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is ahead \Non JW Broadcasting for August 2016.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.77,0:01:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s theme is taken \Nfrom David’s poetic song to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.00,0:01:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 18:25, which states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“With someone loyal you act in loyalty.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.84,0:01:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hebrew term “act in loyalty” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.28,0:01:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,reminds us \Nof God’s loyal love\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.71,0:01:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is love motivated \Nby commitment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.15,0:01:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity, loyalty, \Nand deep attachment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.19,0:01:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So loyalty is more \Nthan just a feeling; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.46,0:01:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is active; \Nit’s rooted in love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How comforting it is \Nto know that Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.00,0:01:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingly attaches himself \Nto those who are loyal to him!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.33,0:02:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But what motivated David \Nto write the words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.04,0:02:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 18:25? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.11,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The superscription reveals \Nthat it was composed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,after “Jehovah rescued him \Nfrom the hand of all his enemies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.91,0:02:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the hand of Saul.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.05,0:02:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the great joy \Nand relief he must have felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.72,0:02:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,after experiencing firsthand \NJehovah’s loyal love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.75,0:02:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and mighty saving acts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.12,0:02:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, throughout his life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,David experienced \Ndisloyalty at its worst: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.23,0:02:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,from his king, Saul; \Nfrom his wife Michal; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.97,0:02:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from his trusted counselor Ahithophel; \Nand from his son Absalom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.94,0:02:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt the deep hurt of betrayal \Nby those he trusted and loved most.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Loyalty is a choice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.78,0:02:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we find when we look back \Nat David’s life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.22,0:02:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,David chose to stay loyal to God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From a humble shepherd boy \Ncaring for his sheep \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.22,0:02:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to a valiant king \Ncaring for the nation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.99,0:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he proved \Nto be someone loyal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a man agreeable \Nto Jehovah’s heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can be a real test \Nto maintain loyalty to God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when we face injustices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.40,0:03:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the desperate situation \Nthat David and his mighty warriors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.47,0:03:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced when they \Nwere fugitives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.74,0:03:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,forced to hide in the wilderness, \Noften low on provisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.81,0:03:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They saw firsthand \NKing Saul’s jealous rage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.82,0:03:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But what choice did David make \Nwhen urged by his men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.29,0:03:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to seize the opportunity \Nto take Saul’s life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.59,0:03:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what David told his men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 24:6: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is unthinkable \Nfrom Jehovah’s standpoint \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.33,0:03:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I should do \Nsuch a thing to my lord, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“the anointed of Jehovah, \Nby lifting my hand against him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.67,0:03:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for he is the anointed of Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.71,0:03:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,David knew that if he remained loyal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.22,0:03:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would remain loyal to him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,—He would show him loyal love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He humbly put aside \Nhis personal feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.72,0:04:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and viewed matters \Nfrom Jehovah’s perspective. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.66,0:04:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He chose to wait patiently \Nfor Jehovah to “act in loyalty.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll soon be facing \Nlife-changing events foretold in the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that will test our loyalty \Nto Jehovah and his organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.74,0:04:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So now is the time \Nto strengthen our loyalty! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As we do, we can be sure \Nthat Jehovah knows our circumstances\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.15,0:04:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps injustices \Nwe have experienced—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.02,0:04:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and will reward our loyal service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.29,0:04:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So ask yourself, ‘What loyal actions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will motivate Jehovah to be loyal to me?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider three areas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we can be loyal \Nto Jehovah by defending him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah is \Nthe Sovereign of the universe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we come to his defense? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.74,0:04:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can learn how \Nfrom the fine example of Elihu! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.28,0:04:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book of Job, \NElihu listened patiently as Job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.85,0:05:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and his three false comforters spoke. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.95,0:05:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Elihu’s reaction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.12,0:05:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at Job 32:2, 3: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.92,0:05:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“His anger blazed against Job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.93,0:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“for trying to prove himself \Nright rather than God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“He was also very angry \Nwith Job’s three companions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.80,0:05:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“because they could not find an answer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but had declared God wicked.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.74,0:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A fire of righteous indignation \Nwas burning inside young Elihu. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In Job 36:2, 3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.91,0:05:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,he loyally comes \Nto Jehovah’s defense saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be patient with me \Na little longer while I explain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.35,0:05:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“for I still have words \Nto speak on God’s behalf. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will speak comprehensively \Nabout what I know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will ascribe \Nrighteousness to my Maker.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Elihu courageously proved loyal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.70,0:05:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by praising, \Nand, yes, defending God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:05:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we need to come \Nto Jehovah’s defense today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.61,0:06:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our loving heavenly Father\Nis blasphemed in so many ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,False religions claim \Nthat he’s part of a Trinity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.95,0:06:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he torments people \Neternally in burning hell. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.45,0:06:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Others say that he \Ndoes not exist or if he does, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.92,0:06:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he doesn’t really care about us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.99,0:06:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that such lies \Ncome from Satan the Devil. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We demonstrate our loyalty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by speaking in defense of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.17,0:06:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thereby proving \NSatan the liar that he is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.30,0:06:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We boldly and zealously proclaim \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.87,0:06:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that he does exist \Nas the almighty God; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.68,0:06:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he is \Nwise, just, and loving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.11,0:06:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he will soon \Nbring an end to all evil \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.75,0:06:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and reward his loyal ones \Nwith eternal life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah could make \Nthe stones cry out in defense, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.36,0:06:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,yet he honors his loyal Witnesses\N—you and me—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with this fine privilege.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we can be loyal \Nto Jehovah by being loyal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:07:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to “the faithful and discreet slave,” \Nthe Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah and Jesus are using \N“the faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to feed us spiritually, \Nso we owe our loyalty to that slave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But some may say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.95,0:07:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Isn’t the Governing Body \Nmade up of imperfect men?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.98,0:07:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.99,0:07:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The last perfect person to walk \Nthe earth was Jesus himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no perfect person \Nor organization on the globe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.49,0:07:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a long-time faithful brother \Nused to say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.20,0:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is the best imperfect organization \Non earth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus didn’t say \Nthe slave would be infallible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.07,0:07:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it would be \Nfaithful and discreet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.91,0:07:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we listen to \Nand obey the faithful slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.34,0:07:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,has a direct bearing on the strength \Nof our friendship with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it means our very life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.72,0:07:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,serves some spiritual food \Nthat is not to our liking? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what if we do not fully understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.19,0:08:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or agree with a clarification of a belief? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.03,0:08:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On one occasion, Jesus’ followers, \Nincluding the apostle Peter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,were confronted \Nwith a new teaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How did most react? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice John 6:60, it states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.34,0:08:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“When they heard this, \Nmany of his disciples said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This speech is shocking;\Nwho can listen to it?’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.59,0:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuing in verse 66: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because of this, \Nmany of his disciples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.66,0:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,went off to the things behind \Nand would no longer walk with him.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.26,0:08:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did Peter respond \Nwhen Jesus asked them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.17,0:08:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Are you too stumbled?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 6:68, we read: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.80,0:08:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Simon Peter answered him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.17,0:08:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Lord, whom shall we go away to? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You have sayings of everlasting life.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.61,0:08:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What loyalty! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter’s loyalty \Nwas based on solid evidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus was the Messiah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,His loyalty \Nwas evidence of his faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.56,0:09:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the kind of loyalty \Nwe want to imitate today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.46,0:09:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are times we must wait on \NJehovah to clarify matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, \Nmay we prove ourselves loyal like Peter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and follow closely \Nthe lead of the faithful slave, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,who closely follow \Nin the footsteps of their Master, Jesus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.85,0:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, though, we receive \Ncounsel that touches us personally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, on JW Broadcasting \Nwe’ve received loving reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.72,0:09:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from members of the Governing Body \Nto be forgiving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.86,0:09:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to honor Jehovah \Nwith our valuable things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.56,0:09:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and to remain spiritually alert. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.50,0:09:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Through The Watchtower \Nand at Christian meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re reminded to be careful \Nabout our dress and grooming, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose good associates \Nand wholesome entertainment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and to remain morally clean. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.38,0:09:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we quick to respond \Nand make needed adjustments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.81,0:10:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or do we find ourselves wanting \Nto defend our personal rights? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.65,0:10:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A situation \Nin the apostle Paul’s life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.95,0:10:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,tested his loyalty \Nto theocratic direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s found in Acts chapter 21. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.99,0:10:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As you recall, \NPaul arrived in Jerusalem in 56 C.E. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,after a very successful missionary tour. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.40,0:10:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine his excitement \Nas he related in detail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.94,0:10:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“the things God did among \Nthe nations through his ministry.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.54,0:10:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,After hearing \NPaul’s extraordinary account, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.78,0:10:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the older men revealed to Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a problem in Judea \Nthat involved him personally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.98,0:10:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Read what they said \Nat Acts 21:21: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.52,0:10:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“But they [the Jewish believers] \Nhave heard it rumored about you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“that you have been teaching \Nall the Jews \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.13,0:10:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“among the nations \Nan apostasy from Moses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“telling them \Nnot to circumcise their children\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.77,0:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or to follow the customary practices.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, perhaps Paul thought, \N‘Me, an apostate? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Really? \NHow can they say such a thing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.48,0:11:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I just finished \Nmy third missionary tour, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.98,0:11:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and look how \NJehovah blessed the work!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the older men \Ngave Paul very clear direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.99,0:11:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at Acts 21:23, 24 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that he likely did not anticipate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.49,0:11:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and there it reads: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“So do what we tell you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have four men who have put \Nthemselves under a vow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take these men with you \Nand cleanse yourself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.27,0:11:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“ceremonially together with them \Nand take care of their expenses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that they may have \Ntheir heads shaved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then everyone will know \Nthat there is nothing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the rumors \Nthey were told about you,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.28,0:11:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but that you are walking orderly \Nand you are also keeping the Law.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this the time \Nfor Paul to question \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,their decision \Nor demand his rights? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have reasoned: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.62,0:11:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Didn’t you read my letter \Nto the Galatians, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,‘where it says the Law was nailed \Nto the torture stake with Jesus? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.46,0:11:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I did nothing wrong! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.47,0:11:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why do I have to put on \Nthis pretense \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.83,0:12:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,just because a few \Nare overly sensitive?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.17,0:12:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He humbly did \Nas they requested, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,although it \Nnearly cost him his life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.91,0:12:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it meant swallowing his pride, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.71,0:12:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but Paul knew \Nthere were bigger issues \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.82,0:12:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,involved than his personal rights. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He was considerate \Nof the consciences of others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But more importantly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he showed his loyalty to Jehovah \Nand to the governing body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we see \Nthe bigger issue in our life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us be determined \Nto be humble,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.47,0:12:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,flexible, \Nand obedient like Paul, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby \Nprove ourselves faithful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to “the faithful and discreet slave.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Third, we can be loyal to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by being loyal to the elders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.72,0:12:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve discussed loyalty to Jehovah himself \Nand to the faithful slave,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but what about direction \Nwe receive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.09,0:12:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from the elders \Nin our congregation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.99,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We listen \Nto our elders give talks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and comments \Nat the meetings each week, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we work with them \Nin the ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and we associate \Nwith them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.20,0:13:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This regular contact \Ngives us more opportunities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to see their imperfections \Nand flaws. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.81,0:13:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We could begin to focus \Non their weaknesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.01,0:13:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,weakening our trust \Nin God’s arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if you zoom in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on any of our pictures \Nin our magazines, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.59,0:13:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,all you’ll see are colored spots or pixels. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.09,0:13:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you zoom out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.09,0:13:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a beautiful photo or painting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, when looking at our elders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.43,0:13:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t zoom in on their imperfections\N—the spots of ink—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.97,0:13:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, see the big picture.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.17,0:13:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then, is it so important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.84,0:13:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to strengthen our loyalty \Nto our hard-working, loving shepherds? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.28,0:13:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these “gifts in men” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.38,0:13:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are an expression \Nof Jehovah’s loyal love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.38,0:13:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as they loyally lead, feed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.15,0:13:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and protect \Nhis precious sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.65,0:14:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As the great tribulation nears, \Nour survival will depend \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,on our readiness \Nto respond to their direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as they follow \Nthe Governing Body’s direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.80,0:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Our loyalty is not to men, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but to Jehovah’s arrangement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,made up of imperfect, \Nbut loyal men.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.47,0:14:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a lesson \Nthat Korah, Dathan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and Abiram refused to learn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In this clip from the video \NRespect Jehovah’s Authority, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,listen to Korah’s defiant attitude \Ntoward Moses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.15,0:14:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as taken \Nfrom Numbers chapter 16.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s Moses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That is enough of you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because the whole assembly \Nare all of them holy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.53,0:14:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah is in their midst. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then, should you lift yourselves up \Nabove the congregation of Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.91,0:14:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Korah and the others \Nmade great pretenses of loyalty to God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.51,0:15:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but completely ignored the fact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.02,0:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah directly appointed \NMoses and Aaron. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who, then, were \Nthey really murmuring against? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.89,0:15:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Numbers 26:9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.96,0:15:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“This Dathan and Abiram \Nwere chosen ones of the assembly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“who fought against Moses \Nand Aaron along with Korah’s group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.20,0:15:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when they fought against Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.14,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,While focusing on the man Moses \Nand his imperfections, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they did not really see that it was Jehovah \Nwho was directing the nation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.05,0:15:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They were actually fighting \Nagainst Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.59,0:15:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Their disloyalty to God’s appointed men\Ncost them their lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But Korah’s sons \Nmade a different choice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.83,0:15:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In this next clip, notice an attitude \Nfar different from their father’s.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.50,0:15:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My father and his companions\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,actually rebelled \Nagainst Jehovah’s authority.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:15:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their envy, pride, \Nand ambition led to rebellion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.21,0:16:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the end they brought \Ndishonor upon themselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My father sought glory, \Nbut his glory was short-lived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.52,0:16:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m glad, though, that my brothers \Nand I took the right side of the issue.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been hard though.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.92,0:16:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.53,0:16:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But that helps us to understand \Nhow important it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we do not allow \Nfriendships or family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to take priority \Nover our relationship with Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and our obedience to him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Father \Nhas always told me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.34,0:16:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm, yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.71,0:16:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, successful direction \Nfor us humans \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.25,0:16:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We should completely trust \Nin his choices of appointed ones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.55,0:16:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, respect for those \Nwhom Jehovah has appointed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.72,0:16:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,shows respect \Nfor Jehovah’s authority.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.33,0:16:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The loyalty displayed by Korah’s sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.73,0:17:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,moved Jehovah to act \Nin loyalty by sparing their lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What fine examples \Nfor us to imitate! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.47,0:17:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,May we never find ourselves \Nfighting against Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.84,0:17:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by murmuring \Nor complaining against those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.01,0:17:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who he has appointed \Nto lead his people today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To see more \Nof the good and the bad examples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.35,0:17:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of loyalty \Namong the Israelites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.42,0:17:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we encourage you to watch the entire \NRespect Jehovah’s Authority video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on JW Broadcasting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In review, how can we show \Nour loyalty to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.16,0:17:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First, by coming to his defense \Nas his Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.70,0:17:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, by maintaining our loyal support \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of “the faithful and discreet slave.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, by loyally following direction \Nfrom the appointed elders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.71,0:17:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you imitate faithful examples \Nlike the sons of Korah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,like David, Peter, and Paul, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.59,0:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you will prove to be someone \NJehovah views as loyal\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.96,0:17:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—worthy of receiving \Nhis acts of loyalty forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our second point on loyalty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.90,0:18:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,shows us ways we can follow \Nthe faithful and discreet slave’s direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But have you ever wondered how \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.70,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body arrives \Nat important decisions? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In this Bethel morning worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother David Splane \Nanswers that very question.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.64,0:18:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, there’ve been so many changes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.21,0:18:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s hard to keep up.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We hear that a lot. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.45,0:18:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the question is, \NHow do these changes come about? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.56,0:18:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the Governing Body get together \Non a Wednesday morning and say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.56,0:18:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, what will we change \Nthis week? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.83,0:18:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s throw the brotherhood \Noff guard a little bit.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.33,0:18:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That would not be \Nfaithful or discreet.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,although changes may seem \Nto be announced one after another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.44,0:18:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the decision to put \Nthe changes into effect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.85,0:18:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is often years in the making. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.35,0:18:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one of the first big changes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.85,0:19:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that the current Governing Body \Nhad to grapple with \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.86,0:19:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.86,0:19:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it feasible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a Branch Committee serving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.86,0:19:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.87,0:19:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for years the thought was \Nthat we really couldn’t have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a Branch Committee \Nfunctioning in the United States \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.31,0:19:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because the States was host \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.11,0:19:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Governing Body \Nand the world headquarters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.28,0:19:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was going to be \Na big decision, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.78,0:19:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wasn’t taken overnight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of consultation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with mature, \Nexperienced brothers was necessary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But finally the decision was made, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.23,0:19:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we believe that decision \Nhas had Jehovah’s rich blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.56,0:19:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re proud \Nof our hard-working Branch Committee, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.10,0:19:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re happy \Nto have their support. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.47,0:19:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We need their support.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider \Na couple of other examples. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Beginning in the first week \Nof January 2009, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the School, Service Meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.55,0:20:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Congregation Book Study \Nwere merged. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.42,0:20:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that decision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.42,0:20:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,was almost ten years \Nin the making. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As far back as 1999, \Nit was being discussed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then, why wasn’t the decision \Nmade ten years earlier? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Governing Body \Nwanted to be sure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.30,0:20:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the brothers \Nhave what they need? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.31,0:20:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they have \Nall of the spiritual food they need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.31,0:20:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if we merge the meetings?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then one Wednesday\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—I think it was \Nabout three-thirty in the afternoon—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d had a long meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We received two letters \Nfrom large branches. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.62,0:20:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the branches said \Nthat they had many large congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with seven or eight book studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but with only one elder \Nand one ministerial servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.60,0:20:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the elder might conduct \Nfive book studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ministerial servant \Nmight conduct three, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.27,0:20:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they had all of the parts \Non the meetings to prepare. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:21:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So all they were doing with their time \Nwas conducting book studies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.14,0:21:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and preparing parts \Nfor the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.88,0:21:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the same week we received \Na letter from another branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.19,0:21:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and they explained why the attendance \Nat the book study was so low. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.49,0:21:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They explained that the publishers \Nloved the meetings\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of the meetings—\Nincluding the book study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.33,0:21:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But they’re very poor, \Nand they couldn’t afford the bus fare \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.13,0:21:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend two midweek meetings; \Nthey had to choose. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they attended \Nthe School and Service Meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.41,0:21:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they could get almost two hours \Nof spiritual direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas with the book study, \Nthey would get one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So most of the time \Nit was the School \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.32,0:21:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and Service Meeting \Nthat won out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.22,0:21:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those two letters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.86,0:21:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,put a real face \Non the situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.36,0:21:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helped us \Nto make the decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.40,0:21:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in 2008, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.56,0:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a public edition \Nand a study edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:22:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of The Watchtower \Nbegan to be published. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.27,0:22:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That decision was \Na long time coming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.44,0:22:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We discussed the possibility off and on, \Nbut we always said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.08,0:22:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let’s not be hasty; \Nlet’s wait a little bit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.58,0:22:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what Jehovah wants.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The main thing was, \NWhat would Jehovah want? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.02,0:22:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And how would we know? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.02,0:22:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided to make \Na sort of fleece test. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.99,0:22:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so in 2006, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we began publishing \None Awake! a month, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.46,0:22:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but we kept publishing \Ntwo Watchtowers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.60,0:22:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be three magazines \Nper month, instead of four.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.34,0:22:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rationale was, \N“We’ll try it for a year,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.44,0:22:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“and if at the end of a year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.44,0:22:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“our magazine placements \Nhave plummeted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“we’ll know that Jehovah \Nis not backing this arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.68,0:22:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go back to producing \Ntwo Awakes! a year.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.58,0:22:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.62,0:22:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.62,0:22:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we were placing \Nas many magazines at three per month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.49,0:23:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as we had been placing \Nat four per month the year before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.73,0:23:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that indicated to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.03,0:23:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah \Nwas backing the arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.37,0:23:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And how many \Nof us have appreciated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.37,0:23:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,having a study edition \Nof The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that speaks directly \Nto the brotherhood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.71,0:23:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a public edition \Nof The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.14,0:23:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be tailored \Na little bit more \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.48,0:23:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to the needs of the public.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.05,0:23:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, before making \Nany decision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that affects \Nthe Kingdom work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.92,0:23:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body \Nhas to carefully consider \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual implications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, \Nin 2008, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.36,0:23:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the decision was made to reduce \Nthe length of public talks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.16,0:23:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from 45 minutes \Nto 30 minutes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.47,0:23:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well you say, ‘How could \Nthat decision possibly affect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.94,0:23:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirituality \Nof the brotherhood?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.87,0:23:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’re serving \Nin an urban congregation with many elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.38,0:23:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and nearby there are other \Nurban congregations with many elders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.72,0:23:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps you’d have difficulty \Nin understanding the reasoning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.42,0:24:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Governing Body \Nhas to look at the whole picture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.86,0:24:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of our brothers \Nhave served where the need is great, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.19,0:24:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’ve learned \Na foreign language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.10,0:24:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And in many, many \Nof these congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.50,0:24:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the learners are the elders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.63,0:24:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the learners \Nhave told us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.94,0:24:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that for every minute \Nof a public talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.21,0:24:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it has required one hour \Nof preparation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.68,0:24:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you imagine: \N45-minute public talk\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.05,0:24:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—45 hours for some of them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.52,0:24:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reduction in the length \Nof the public talks has actually meant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that these congregations \Ncould have more public talks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.96,0:24:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.96,0:24:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There are thousands of elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.23,0:24:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who are serving \Nin isolated congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.50,0:24:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that may be 100 miles or more \Nfrom the next congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.33,0:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So in one congregation \Nyou have one elder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.77,0:24:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then 100 miles away you have \Nanother congregation with one elder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.67,0:24:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How many public talks \Nwere those brothers getting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when there were \N45-minute public talks? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.61,0:24:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The 15-minute reduction \Nmade a difference.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.31,0:25:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we take a narrow view \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.32,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and think only about our own situation \Nand our own congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.79,0:25:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we can have difficulty \Nin understanding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.92,0:25:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,why certain decisions are made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.66,0:25:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the same principles \Napply to clarifications in our beliefs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.06,0:25:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body loves \Nto get together and discuss the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.20,0:25:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And when those Bibles \Ncome out on the table \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.30,0:25:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and when the brothers \Nbring their research in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.61,0:25:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re starting to search \Nthe Scriptures and analyze the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.71,0:25:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the happy smiles \Non their faces. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers love \Ndiscussing spiritual things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.11,0:25:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the clarifications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.72,0:25:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are often a long time \Nin coming into print. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.36,0:25:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.86,0:25:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the clarification \Non one scripture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.23,0:25:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can have \Na domino effect on others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.49,0:25:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The clarification \Non one scripture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.76,0:25:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can have ramifications \Non other prophecies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.33,0:25:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so we have to be absolutely sure \Nthat everything fits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.74,0:25:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So to reiterate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.74,0:26:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,although certain changes \Nmay be announced one after another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.74,0:26:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,these decisions \Nare thought out very carefully.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.98,0:26:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s \Nan interesting side point: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.18,0:26:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The older members \Nof the Governing Body\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.65,0:26:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—Brother Jaracz, Brother Barr—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.99,0:26:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,were just as interested \Nin making the adjustments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.36,0:26:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as the younger members were. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.76,0:26:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They were very progressive.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.86,0:26:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What an insight into the faithful \Nand discreet slave’s loving concern! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.47,0:26:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear things \Nthe Governing Body does \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.80,0:26:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would further motivate you \Nto support and follow their direction? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.21,0:26:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it’s how \Nthey consulted experienced brothers; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.54,0:26:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or that they consider our brothers’ \Nvarying circumstances worldwide; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.55,0:26:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or, most importantly, \Nhow they patiently and prayerfully seek \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.89,0:26:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to know Jehovah’s will \Nand look for his blessing on a decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.62,0:26:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of our brothers \Nand sisters around the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.36,0:26:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,can recount \Nthe blessings they’ve gained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.39,0:26:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by remaining loyal \Nto Jehovah and his organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.06,0:27:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re privileged to have \Ntwo such examples here with us today: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.67,0:27:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister \NWilliam and Sandra Malenfant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Malenfant is a helper \Nto the Teaching Committee, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.84,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sister Malenfant’s current assignment \Nis in the Service Department. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.38,0:27:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re looking forward to hearing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.61,0:27:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about their rich spiritual history.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.55,0:27:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Bill and Sandra, \Nwe’re so happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.82,0:27:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could have you \Nhere in the studio with us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.99,0:27:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and we do look forward \Nto learning more about you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.76,0:27:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we would like \Nto go back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.63,0:27:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you get \Non the road that has led you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.23,0:27:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to so many years of faithful, \Nloyal service to Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.07,0:27:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was back in 1954. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.74,0:27:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother had contact on and off \Nwith the Witnesses for years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.67,0:27:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about 20 years old, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.71,0:27:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was invited \Nto a public talk \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.24,0:27:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Oakland Central Congregation \Nin California. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.88,0:27:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked me, \N“Would you accompany me?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.18,0:27:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said: “Yeah. \NSure, I’ll be happy to go.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.22,0:27:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I recognized a young man \NI knew from high school at the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.52,0:27:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and he approached me after \Nand told me I needed a Bible study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.19,0:28:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn’t want a Bible study, \Nbut he insisted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.63,0:28:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I said, \N“Well, you can come by.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.73,0:28:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you believe it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.00,0:28:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I started a Bible study \Nin the “Let God Be True” book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.00,0:28:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Four months later, \NI was baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.31,0:28:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was exactly what I was looking for, \Nbut I didn’t realize it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.14,0:28:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Good choice. \NThank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.31,0:28:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And, Sandra, your start on the road \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.38,0:28:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to a career serving Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.75,0:28:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I was born, my parents \Nstarted on this search for the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.75,0:28:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened because they \Nhad lost a little girl in death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.32,0:28:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and they went from church to church \Nlooking for some kind of comfort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.33,0:28:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the clergy \Nhad no comfort for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.83,0:28:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They just said, “Well, God wanted \Nanother angel in heaven.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.07,0:28:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And that angered my father. \NHe thought: ‘No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.87,0:28:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If God wants another angel, \Nhe can make one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.97,0:28:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn’t take my little girl!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.97,0:28:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So it just happened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.98,0:28:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that one evening \Nthey were listening to the radio\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.25,0:28:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—long before TV, of course—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.25,0:28:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and they heard \Na Jehovah’s Witness give a talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.35,0:29:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And the title of that talk was \N“Where Are the Dead?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.59,0:29:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.86,0:29:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave all the Scriptural proof \Nabout the condition of the dead \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.63,0:29:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hope for the resurrection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.96,0:29:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And my father immediately said, \N“This is the truth!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.80,0:29:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So they wrote \Nto the radio station; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.14,0:29:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,got a copy \Nof the booklet of the talk; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.81,0:29:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, also, \Nthey started receiving \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.97,0:29:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the subscription \Nto The Watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.54,0:29:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wasn’t until I was born \Nand three years old \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.41,0:29:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Witnesses \Nfinally made contact with us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.22,0:29:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what motivated you \Nto make a choice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.02,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to get into the full-time service \Nand give your life to Jehovah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what motivated me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.99,0:29:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was when I attended \Na convention, also in ’56. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.50,0:29:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized in ’54. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.80,0:29:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But in ’56, I went to a district convention \Nin Albany, California, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.90,0:29:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was a pioneer booth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.77,0:29:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I approached the booth, \Nand an older sister there looked at me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.11,0:29:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and said: \N“You’re young and strong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.11,0:29:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t you a pioneer?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.84,0:29:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt, ‘Well, yes. \NWhy not?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.88,0:30:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started \Npioneering in 1956. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.45,0:30:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what motivated me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.58,0:30:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was— \NReally, I look back at that; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.12,0:30:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it was one of the best decisions \NI made in my life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.72,0:30:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandra, how about you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.49,0:30:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Motivated to get \Ninto full-time service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.26,0:30:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for pioneer service, you know, \Nit was—it was like a given. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.80,0:30:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Young people were \Njust encouraged to pioneer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.50,0:30:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And most of the young people \Nwere doing that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.24,0:30:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, after a year or two, maybe they \Nwould get married and start a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.71,0:30:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But those years in pioneering\N—starting out their life that way—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.31,0:30:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,gave them a wonderful basis \Nfor loyal service the rest of their life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.05,0:30:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.72,0:30:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.38,0:30:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How did your paths \Neventually meet?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.92,0:30:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at a circuit assembly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.99,0:30:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in Oakland, California, 1956. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.23,0:30:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting things \Ntook place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.50,0:30:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the job \Nof dismantling the stage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was carrying \Nthis large piece of plywood off the stage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.24,0:30:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and I ran right into Sandra \Nand knocked her flat! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.07,0:30:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I took advantage \Nof the opportunity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.44,0:31:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, ‘Well, that’s not \Nthe best way to introduce yourself.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.81,0:31:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But I said, “By the way, \Nwould you like to accompany me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.95,0:31:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to a get-together \Nsome of the friends are having?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.12,0:31:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good, Bill.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.25,0:31:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, \Nand I followed through on it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.99,0:31:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a lot \Nof association, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.99,0:31:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and after a number of months, \Nwe got married. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.36,0:31:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And both of us \Nwere pioneering\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.39,0:31:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,—very happy in our ministry \Nserving Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.93,0:31:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You really swept her off her feet. \NLiterally.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.36,0:31:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I fell for him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.36,0:31:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.33,0:31:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shortly after you were married, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.97,0:31:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand \Nthat you received some direction.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.84,0:31:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the circuit overseer \Nvisited our congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.17,0:31:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We were only married about a month, \NI think, when he came through.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.41,0:31:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he told us that the organization \Nwas looking for pioneers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.88,0:31:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who’d be willing to serve \Nas special pioneers and go wherever,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.92,0:31:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where the need was great \Nin the United States particularly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.12,0:31:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we told him: \N“Sure. We’d be delighted to do it.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.69,0:31:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And four months \Nafter our marriage,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.26,0:31:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we received an assignment \Nas special pioneers to Decorah, Iowa.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.86,0:31:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that was \Na very interesting place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.70,0:32:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because there were \Nonly eight publishers in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.70,0:32:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But we arrived \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.77,0:32:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and started with the meetings there \Nat the Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.31,0:32:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Kingdom Hall was up \Nabove Hunt’s Variety Store \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.14,0:32:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in downtown Decorah, \Nand we lived in a room behind it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.05,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, \Nyou’re on your own like that\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,—not a lot of brothers around—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.12,0:32:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so you look \Nfor encouragement and company. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.25,0:32:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would travel down \Nto Strawberry Point, Iowa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.73,0:32:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to where \NCharles and Shirley Sinutko lived \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.10,0:32:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a log cabin\N—one-room log cabin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.00,0:32:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’d go visit with them in order \Nto have some mutual encouragement.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.07,0:32:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a nice picture of you \Nin that log cabin too \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.27,0:32:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as you were \Nspecial pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.27,0:32:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’re busy \Nin that work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.81,0:32:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What special invitation \Ndid you receive?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.48,0:32:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we received \Nthe invitation to attend Gilead\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.88,0:32:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—the 34th class of Gilead School—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.58,0:32:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was a wonderful thing \Nafter two and half years of pioneering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.49,0:32:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,special pioneering in Iowa.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.49,0:32:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were assigned \Nto Lebanon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.59,0:33:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but we were unable to enter Lebanon \Nbecause we couldn’t get the visa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.80,0:33:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, the organization \Nasked us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.93,0:33:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, will you take \Nan assignment to Morocco?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.33,0:33:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We were ready to go anywhere.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.87,0:33:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s how we took \Na boat from New York City\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.94,0:33:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,—five days across the Atlantic—\Nto Casablanca.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.04,0:33:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was it like to be \Nin the missionary service in Morocco?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.71,0:33:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very interesting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.41,0:33:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We really enjoyed it. \NBut, you know, we only spoke English. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.68,0:33:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So in Morocco, \Nwe had to learn French. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.05,0:33:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first month \Nof our missionary service in Morocco, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.92,0:33:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for 30 days we studied \Nthe language 11 hours a day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.30,0:33:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that could get pretty tiring \Nfor 11 hours a day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.27,0:33:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so we’d go to the French movies \Nand count that as language time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.87,0:33:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, we were moved \Nto Tangier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.24,0:33:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was \Na Spanish congregation in Tangier, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.57,0:33:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to learn \Nthe Spanish language too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.58,0:33:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was \Nreally a rich blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.31,0:33:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for the two of us \Nto be exposed to that culture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.05,0:33:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and to have \Nthat privilege of serving there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.55,0:34:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So after four years, I understand \Nthat you came back to visit your family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.29,0:34:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What events \Nwere challenging thereafter?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.36,0:34:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Sandra can relate that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.83,0:34:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was \Nusually permitted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.63,0:34:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that after you were \Nin your assignment four years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.63,0:34:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then you were allowed \Nto come home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.63,0:34:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and at least have a vacation \Nand visit your family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.74,0:34:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But we got back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.74,0:34:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We visited our family, \Nand while there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.88,0:34:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a medical examination and found out \Nthat I had a serious health problem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.25,0:34:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we didn’t have \Nthe funds to cover that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.48,0:34:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So Bill wrote to the Society, \Nand we made arrangements. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.35,0:34:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, \N“Well, just take care of your situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.19,0:34:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and let us know when you’re free.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.32,0:34:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So he got a job \Nto take care \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.16,0:34:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of our medical needs \Nas well as living conditions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.60,0:34:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, \Nwe just felt like we were failures.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.07,0:34:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knew \Nwe were discouraged. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.87,0:34:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew we felt \Ndistraught about this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.27,0:34:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So he knew just what we needed, \Nand he gave it to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.84,0:34:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As I got to feeling better \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.91,0:34:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got more free \Nin our use of time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.61,0:35:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we started pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.62,0:35:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah blessed \Nour ministry just incredibly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.59,0:35:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There were times, \Nin this supposedly “unproductive territory” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.59,0:35:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that we had up to 25 people \Nattending the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.69,0:35:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them got baptized, \Nand they’re our fast friends to this day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.47,0:35:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s incredible!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.30,0:35:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah knows what you need, \Nand he provides it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.60,0:35:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That is beautiful! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.60,0:35:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What temptation \Ndid you have to resist \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.91,0:35:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when you came back \Nand were going through these difficulties?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.71,0:35:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think it’s \Na temptation that confronts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.91,0:35:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of brothers and sisters \Nwho return because of health reasons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.72,0:35:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and some just end up settling down \Nbecause of their circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.86,0:35:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But the temptation there was: \N‘Well, you’re home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.49,0:35:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You’ve already done your service \Nin Morocco for a number of years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.03,0:35:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You’ve been \Nin the full-time ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.60,0:35:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just settle down now. \NBuy a house.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.53,0:35:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, \Nthat wasn’t our desire. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.30,0:35:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So as soon as Sandra \Ngot on her feet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.40,0:35:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and was feeling well enough, \Nwe got pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.04,0:36:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I wrote headquarters, \Nand I said: ‘Here we are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.51,0:36:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We’re ready to take on whatever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.51,0:36:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you like us to do?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.11,0:36:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good example. \NThank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.75,0:36:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you made yourself \Navailable to the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.55,0:36:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did they send you next?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.55,0:36:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.02,0:36:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were sent \Nas special pioneers to Washington D.C., \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.96,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to help start \Na Spanish congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.30,0:36:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was indeed \Na very rich blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.77,0:36:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We were there \Na year and a half \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.13,0:36:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,until that little congregation \Nwas solid and was formed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.11,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we received \Nanother blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We were appointed \Nto the circuit work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.94,0:36:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had the Spanish circuit in Florida \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.58,0:36:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,from Key West to Orlando\N—one circuit in the whole state. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we came to New York City\N—lived in the Bronx. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.49,0:36:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a circuit, and we did \Ndistrict work in the Spanish field. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.79,0:36:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, to Texas\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.79,0:36:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—to what they call the Valley of Texas, \Nthe Rio Grande Valley—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.73,0:36:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of years in the circuit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.73,0:36:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the district in Spanish \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.30,0:37:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from Houston, Texas, \Nto Yuba City, California. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.44,0:37:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we loved \Nevery minute of it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.94,0:37:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s definitely \Nthe traveling work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.47,0:37:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then 1977 rolls around \Nand you receive another invitation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.41,0:37:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.51,0:37:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We were doing \Npreconvention work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.75,0:37:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in the L.A. area \Nat the Leimert Assembly Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.05,0:37:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and we received a letter \Ninviting us to come to Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.39,0:37:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very, very special privilege: \Nto be invited to Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.36,0:37:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into the Service Department, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.36,0:37:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because at that time they \Ninvited a number of traveling overseers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.20,0:37:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to come in and work \Nin the Service Department, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.63,0:37:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sandra went \Ninto housekeeping. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.97,0:37:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were both \Ndelighted to come to Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.71,0:37:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sort of. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.04,0:37:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I really loved the ministry; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.31,0:37:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved, especially, \Nthe district work\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.81,0:37:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—being with \Nthe circuit overseer and his wife\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.82,0:37:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,, every week \Nand out in service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.25,0:37:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wasn’t too anxious \Nfor this Bethel thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.49,0:37:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know. \NJehovah, again, knows what you need. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.36,0:38:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We came here, and we \Nstarted adjusting to Bethel life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.50,0:38:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it really proved out \Nto be a real blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.80,0:38:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because we got \Nthe close association \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.84,0:38:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with so many \Nother loyal Witnesses of Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.91,0:38:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m sure you \Nhave many more experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.44,0:38:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to let us know about, \Nbut we appreciate you sharing those. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.88,0:38:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body \Nhas made significant adjustments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.68,0:38:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the work that is taking place \Nat Bethel and the field, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.96,0:38:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has affected \Nmany long-time faithful brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.19,0:38:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—loyal brothers \Nin the traveling work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.69,0:38:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,overseers in the congregation, \Noverseers at Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.63,0:38:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill, what do you think \Nabout some of these changes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.57,0:38:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Governing Body \Nhas made recently?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.57,0:38:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they’re \Nvery wise decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.64,0:38:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They know what is needed; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.81,0:38:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they appreciate the older men \Nwho have served for years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.71,0:38:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the older brothers \Nin circuit work, district work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.65,0:38:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever, they’re “worthy of double honor” \Nbecause of the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.09,0:39:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they’ve given \Nof themselves to the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.45,0:39:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have to recognize, too, \Nthere comes a time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.46,0:39:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,when we want the younger men \Nto come along, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.69,0:39:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept responsibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.70,0:39:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, really, \Nwhen we were young, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.90,0:39:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we received responsibilities \Nwith very little background and training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.67,0:39:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we’ve got all these schools \Nfor Kingdom Evangelizers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.07,0:39:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Kingdom Ministry School. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.48,0:39:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So many opportunities \Nfor younger ones to be trained. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.81,0:39:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I think \Nit’s a wonderful arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.88,0:39:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Many thousands of young men \Nare doing so well, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.09,0:39:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,ready to accept responsibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.09,0:39:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a blessing \Nfor the entire organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.56,0:39:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you for sharing that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.22,0:39:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That’ll benefit many brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.29,0:39:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look \Nat this couple before us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.83,0:39:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see some who have made \Nwise choices along the way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.67,0:39:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look back at over 60 years \Nof faithful, loyal service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.37,0:39:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As you look back at decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.37,0:39:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you made in life, any regrets?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.21,0:39:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, absolutely none! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.21,0:39:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We consider that whatever \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.71,0:40:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have given up or done \Nit’s been our gift to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.72,0:40:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I was a little girl, \NI remember I used to go out on our farm \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.22,0:40:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and, especially when there \Nwas a full moon, I used to pray to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.63,0:40:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’d say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.63,0:40:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just let me use up my life in your service.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.50,0:40:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he’s answered \Nthat prayer because my life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.17,0:40:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of it, is used up \Nand he’s let me do it in his service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.71,0:40:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill, how do you view sacrifices \Nthat you have made along the way?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.34,0:40:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as you know, a sacrifice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.35,0:40:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,can be something \Nyou give up to serve God, perhaps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.88,0:40:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a sacrifice can be \Nwhat you give to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.25,0:40:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like David said in Psalm 54. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.26,0:40:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will sacrifice to you willingly.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.49,0:40:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s how I view sacrifice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.69,0:40:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re happy to give of ourselves \Nto Jehovah God—to serve him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.60,0:40:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to add, too, Sandra has been \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.27,0:40:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a wonderful partner with me\N—willing to go anywhere, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.50,0:40:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,put up with all kinds \Nof circumstances and difficulties.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.64,0:41:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A scripture that I— \NThere are a number \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.88,0:41:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of good Scriptures, \Nobviously, that we all love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.18,0:41:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But one in particular \Nthat stays in my mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.81,0:41:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is Romans 14:7,8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.45,0:41:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We live, we live to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.52,0:41:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We die, we die to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.79,0:41:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether we live or we die, \Nwe belong to Jehovah.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.26,0:41:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ve made that decision, \Nnot just because he’s the Creator. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.80,0:41:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve made the decision \Nto give ourselves to Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.27,0:41:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, absolutely, \Nwe’ve had the best life possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.07,0:41:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no regrets at all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.51,0:41:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about what we’ve done with our life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.75,0:41:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,giving Jehovah the first place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.58,0:41:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill and Sandra, \Nit’s been a real privilege \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.58,0:41:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear more about you, and I know \Nthere are more stories to tell. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.69,0:41:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you boil down 60-plus years \Nof loyal service to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.82,0:41:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have given us great insights. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.83,0:41:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for sharing those gems with us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.83,0:41:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the Malenfants, many loyal Witnesses \Nwere not taught the truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.37,0:42:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Bible from birth to adulthood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.17,0:42:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For some young ones, \Nseeds of truth are planted along the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.34,0:42:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but can lay dormant \Nfor years due to family circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.14,0:42:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Cory Wells explains \Nhow her family’s special talent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.05,0:42:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,almost kept her \Nfrom riding on the road to life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.46,0:42:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The first rodeo I performed in front \Nof an audience, I was eight years old.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.80,0:42:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We were considered \None of the top two acts in rodeo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.87,0:42:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My strength lay in my fearlessness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.92,0:42:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though there was \Na certain amount of excitement\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.25,0:42:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—it was fun to travel, \Nto be together as a family—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.99,0:43:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it was empty.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.33,0:43:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Trick riding is like gymnastics \Non the back of a running horse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.97,0:43:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had horses all of our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.94,0:43:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My father specialized in training horses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.84,0:43:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to send us to the mountains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.41,0:43:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,riding all day long. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.85,0:43:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we’d come home \Nin the evening, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.02,0:43:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we would start trick riding.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.96,0:43:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we learned was by a book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.69,0:43:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We looked at stick pictures \Nthat showed how it should be done, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.09,0:43:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and so it was trial and error. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.76,0:43:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time that we were learning,\Nour horses were learning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.63,0:43:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The horse that I rode \Njust let me do anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.14,0:43:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My horse’s name was Sweet Lips. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.14,0:43:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was eight when I got him, \Nand I named him myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.51,0:43:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He was like my best friend.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.28,0:43:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents were very active \Nin the rodeo as competitors. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.05,0:44:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom was barrel racing; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.05,0:44:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,my father was \Na saddle bronc rider. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.92,0:44:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up as \None of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.53,0:44:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I was very young, \Nmaybe six or seven, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.56,0:44:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,my father stopped \Nserving Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.70,0:44:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest with you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.84,0:44:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when they announced that \Nat the Kingdom Hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.24,0:44:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it really didn’t have \Nmuch meaning to me at the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.41,0:44:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what it meant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.04,0:44:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could see people crying, \Nand so I cried. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.81,0:44:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn’t really understand it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.78,0:44:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, from that point, our family \Nwas not active as Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.52,0:44:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up on the road, \Ntraveling rodeo to rodeo\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.29,0:44:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—from coast to coast \Nand from the south to the north—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.36,0:44:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as the roads go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.83,0:44:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The four of us rode initially\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.34,0:44:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—Connie; Kelly; myself; \Nand my brother, Jim. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.67,0:44:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family traveled together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.67,0:44:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That meant a lot to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.18,0:45:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What separated us \Nfrom the others at the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.41,0:45:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was the high speed \Nthat we did it at and also \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.12,0:45:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the difficulty with the tricks \Nthat we chose to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.85,0:45:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,People were very excited. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.86,0:45:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They would hire us back \Nat the same place year after year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.73,0:45:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout all that time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.40,0:45:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we did not miss one Memorial. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.10,0:45:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We were always there. \NThere was something in us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.50,0:45:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn’t know it \Nwhen we were little, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.17,0:45:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but my parents \Nhad succeeded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.21,0:45:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in planting \Nthe truth in our hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.38,0:45:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My link to the truth \Nwas my grandmother. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.81,0:45:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember going \Nto the ranch and visiting her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.32,0:45:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She was very busy, but one thing \Nthat really sticks in my mind\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.49,0:45:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is she always studied\N—every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.29,0:45:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She read her Bible. \NHer magazines were studied. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.10,0:45:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think it just put a seed in there \Nthat later on started to grow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.50,0:45:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I just felt like \NI needed direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:46:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a line \Nwas drawn in the sand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.51,0:46:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Take one path or the other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.68,0:46:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, ironically, \Nthe first book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.25,0:46:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that I picked up \Nto read was the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.58,0:46:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the scriptures \Nthat probably \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.82,0:46:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,meant the most to me \Nwas Proverbs 3:5,6:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.22,0:46:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Trust in Jehovah \Nwith all your heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.39,0:46:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“and do not lean upon \Nyour own understanding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.89,0:46:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“In all your ways \Ntake notice of him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.10,0:46:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he himself \Nwill make your paths straight.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.20,0:46:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to think \Nabout those words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.57,0:46:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what I would have to do \Nto live up to them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.27,0:46:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we traveled \Nwith the rodeo \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.44,0:46:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about ten months \Nout of the year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.48,0:46:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we did go \Nto the district convention, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.48,0:46:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Live Forever book \Ncame out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.55,0:46:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there just came a time \Nwhen I knew\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.55,0:46:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I—I needed to make changes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.32,0:46:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A sister started \Nstudying with me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.56,0:46:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I started reading \Nthe Bible for myself and studying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.96,0:46:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jehovah became real. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.86,0:46:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All it took was one or two people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.90,0:47:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole family followed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.93,0:47:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My father too returned to the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.04,0:47:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Trick riding was our family business. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.04,0:47:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was our livelihood, \Nbut we had decided that we were done. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.75,0:47:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We were going to stop. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.75,0:47:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With that decision would come \Ngiving up everything we knew.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.19,0:47:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think—I think the most difficult thing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.76,0:47:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to do was to sell the horse\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.53,0:47:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—you just, you just get \Nsuch a close bond with them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when you’re putting \Nyour life in their hands like that—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.37,0:47:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was willing to do that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.60,0:47:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I just— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.60,0:47:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what I wanted to do;\NI did it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.71,0:47:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized \Nin October of ʼ85. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.18,0:47:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our last performance \Nwas in February of ʼ86. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.18,0:47:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We just finished out \Nour contracts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.18,0:47:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I started pioneering \Nin September of ʼ86, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.62,0:47:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’ve never stopped.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.06,0:48:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I also married a man \Nwho loves Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.13,0:48:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had \Nthe privilege of working \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.16,0:48:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on international construction projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.16,0:48:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Mexico. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.17,0:48:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Venezuela. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.20,0:48:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is an elder. \NMy mom is pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.51,0:48:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, all of my siblings \Nhave been able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.37,0:48:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to regular pioneer \Nat some point in their lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.41,0:48:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re presently in the circuit work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.08,0:48:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Serving Jehovah together \Nis such a blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.52,0:48:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that we do \Nevery day is for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.32,0:48:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what I wanted to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.33,0:48:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when I made this decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.70,0:48:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If I would have taken \Nthat other path when I was young, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.33,0:48:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I may not be alive today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.07,0:48:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What I did was dangerous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.91,0:48:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even fame and fortune in the world\N—there’s nothing there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.64,0:48:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted “the real life.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.64,0:48:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to serve Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.75,0:48:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no regrets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.85,0:48:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could change anything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.92,0:49:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes \Nto my service to Jehovah,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.42,0:49:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I would change nothing! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.42,0:49:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just do it better.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.53,0:49:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It took courage for Cory and her family \Nto choose loyalty to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.14,0:49:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,over an exciting rodeo career. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.17,0:49:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will always help us \Nwhen we’re prayerfully deciding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.44,0:49:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how an activity or a career we love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.84,0:49:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,affects our dedication to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.88,0:49:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the time it demands, \Nor even the danger involved, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.12,0:49:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,take us away \Nfrom whole-souled service? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.52,0:49:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our loyalty \Nto Jehovah is expressed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.25,0:49:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in how we follow Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.26,0:49:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when making \Nany important decision in life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.29,0:49:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Few decisions are as important \Nas whom we choose to marry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.60,0:49:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Part 1 \Nof our Preparing for Marriage series \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.10,0:49:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared in the May 2016 program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.83,0:49:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In that dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.87,0:49:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a sister realizes she is \Ntoo young for a romantic relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.67,0:49:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and that cultivating \NChristian qualities now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.61,0:49:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,would help her later \Nwhen she’s ready for marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.65,0:50:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Part 2 in the series next depicts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.15,0:50:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,how a dating couple \Ncan successfully know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.22,0:50:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“the secret person of the heart” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.29,0:50:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,so that each can find \Na marriage mate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.29,0:50:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who is loyal to them \Nand to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.45,0:50:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting Ji-min \Nwas completely unexpected. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.12,0:50:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t looking for a girlfriend, \Nbut as we talked, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.59,0:50:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everything just clicked.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.32,0:50:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem is the distance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.19,0:51:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I flew out to see her once, \Nbut most of the time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.10,0:51:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,all we can do \Nis communicate online. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.03,0:51:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I be sure \Nshe’s the one?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.27,0:51:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided the best decision \Nwas to ask my father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.11,0:51:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew the relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.11,0:51:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was becoming more serious, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.41,0:51:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he appreciated my concerns. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.62,0:51:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: \N“The same things are important, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.72,0:51:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“whether the person is next door \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.59,0:51:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“or a world away.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.86,0:51:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Most people simply focus on\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“appearance or social standing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.26,0:52:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“but for a truly successful relationship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.53,0:52:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what matters is spirituality.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.91,0:52:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I had already talked \Nwith Ji-min’s elders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.95,0:52:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and they said she was \Na wonderful pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.72,0:52:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said: “That’s good, \Nbut it takes more than that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.16,0:52:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes time to get to know \N‘the secret person of the heart.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.17,0:52:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do you get to know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.24,0:52:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“the secret person of the heart”?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.51,0:52:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “First, pray. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.18,0:52:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Ask Jehovah \Nto help you see Ji-min \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.98,0:52:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“as she truly is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.35,0:52:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“both her good qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.32,0:52:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and ones \Nthat may need improvement.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.52,0:52:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Also, \Nwhen you are able to visit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.59,0:53:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“observe her actions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.20,0:53:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“How does she treat her friends, \Nher parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.70,0:53:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“ones in the congregation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.43,0:53:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“That’s a good indication of how \Nshe’ll treat you someday.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.37,0:53:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s not just about her.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.84,0:53:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He had me read Ephesians 5:25: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.45,0:53:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Husbands, continue loving your wives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.62,0:53:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as the Christ \Nalso loved the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.99,0:53:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave himself up for it.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.56,0:53:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.69,0:53:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are you ready to be \Nthat kind of husband?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.16,0:53:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought I was \Nbut that the only person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.56,0:53:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that truly knows is me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.34,0:53:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been able to save up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.34,0:53:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a number \Nof visits since then, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.75,0:53:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,taking the time to discover \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.08,0:53:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what we both are spiritually.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.24,0:55:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And while we know we’re not perfect, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.05,0:55:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if we keep our focus on Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.78,0:55:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can be perfect for each other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.96,0:55:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice the ways \Nthey learned more about each other \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.03,0:55:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,before deciding to marry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.03,0:55:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the distance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.04,0:55:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they regularly discussed \Nspiritual matters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.30,0:55:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,arranged for visits \Nchaperoned by trusted adults, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.44,0:55:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and worshipped together \Nat meetings and in the ministry\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.44,0:55:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—all good ways \Nto prepare for marriage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.45,0:55:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The beautiful scene depicting the couple \Nin the metropolitan witnessing work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.18,0:55:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is a reminder of how effective \Nthis form of witnessing has become.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.12,0:55:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We received a report \Nfrom San Francisco, California, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.76,0:55:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.76,0:55:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where publishers have been engaged \Nin special metropolitan witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.23,0:55:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,since 2013. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.30,0:55:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s helping our brothers \Nreach multiple language groups, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.54,0:56:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,start Bible studies, \Nand make disciples.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.12,0:56:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m rolling the carts down \Nto get ready for the work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.09,0:56:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel people’s eyes on me \Nand it makes me feel proud \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.83,0:56:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’m representing Jehovah \Neven before I get to the location.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.73,0:56:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a chance \Nto use our Bibles very regularly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.60,0:56:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk to honesthearted people \Nwho are interested \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.14,0:56:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in really learning \Nwhat the Bible teaches.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.08,0:56:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is reaching people \Nin those hard-to-reach areas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.71,0:56:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where it could mean their life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.78,0:56:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to even talk about things \Nsuch as the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.25,0:56:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re part \Nof the metropolitan work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.76,0:56:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to welcome people \Nbeing drawn by Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.70,0:57:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We see thousands of people \Nevery day who walk by our carts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.67,0:57:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,While we’re placing literature \Nin up to 40 different languages each week, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.24,0:57:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what’s really exciting is to see \Nhow many conversations we’re starting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.21,0:57:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and how many Bible studies \Nwe’re initiating.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.58,0:57:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re visible to a lot of people \Nin the community, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.22,0:57:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,especially those who were inactive \Nor maybe were raised around the truth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.76,0:57:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has arranged \Nto have his people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.96,0:57:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,put right in the center \Nof everything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.76,0:57:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re able to meet people \Nfrom all over the world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.90,0:57:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve met people from Peru, South Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.27,0:57:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan, Germany, England.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.68,0:57:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,France, Italy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.18,0:57:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Cameroon, Congo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.68,0:57:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Beaucoup!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.72,0:57:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In Shona, a greeting \Nwould be something like . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.54,0:58:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . , which means \N“Would you like to study the Bible?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.75,0:58:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . , which means “Would you like \Nto study the Bible?” in sign language.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.38,0:58:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I asked her if she had seen \Nthe sign-language Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.65,0:58:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,she shook her head no, \Nand I showed her Acts 17:27. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.46,0:58:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as it was done, \Nshe started signing, “I understood that!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.93,0:58:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she said, \N“Didn’t you say this was a free app?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.33,0:58:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, right then, \Nshe started downloading it on her phone.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.80,0:58:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a gentleman come up \Nand wanted to . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.54,0:58:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First, he said, “debate,” \Nand then he said, “just discuss.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.31,0:58:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But as he was talking with us, \Nhe had to catch his train \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.71,0:58:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but he missed three trains \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.75,0:58:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because he wanted to continue \Nthe conversation and speak with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.58,0:58:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a really good experience \Nbecause we just get to talk to people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.25,0:59:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and let them see \Na different side of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.49,0:59:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not necessarily about whether\Nwe placed a book with him or not.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.23,0:59:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the end, he turned \Nto my husband and I \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.96,0:59:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and said, “You know, you’re \Nreally good ambassadors.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.86,0:59:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We start Bible studies \Nhere every day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.90,0:59:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and these studies \Nare conducted globally.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.27,0:59:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Alfredo in 2014, \Nright before the Memorial. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.74,0:59:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He approached the cart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.74,0:59:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a rough life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.75,0:59:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He was doing a lot of bad things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.18,0:59:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and so he felt \Nthat he couldn’t overcome them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.78,0:59:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I told him that no matter \Nhow big his problems are, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.99,0:59:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re not too big \Nfor Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.09,0:59:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I encouraged him \Nto start studying the Bible again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.80,0:59:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come, now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.83,0:59:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and let us set matters straight \Nbetween us,” says Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.27,0:59:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“Though your sins are like scarlet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.07,0:59:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they will be made as white as snow.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.91,1:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah forgives you, \Nhe forgives you completely. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.85,1:00:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized, \Nand in the same month, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.85,1:00:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I started auxiliary pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.79,1:00:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is such a privilege to be \None of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.16,1:00:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with brothers \Nall around the world.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.63,1:00:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If anybody is hesitant \Nto take part \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.90,1:00:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the special metropolitan \Nwitnessing work, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.37,1:00:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe you’re worried\Nabout finances, time,\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.77,1:00:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or you’re just afraid \Nthat it’s something different \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.98,1:00:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you won’t know \Nwhat to do, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.61,1:00:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,please don’t let \Nany of those things stop you. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.55,1:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.52,1:00:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab hold of it tight, \Nand don’t let go!\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.84,1:01:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Each month, \Nthe brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.64,1:01:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in San Francisco’s \Nmetropolitan witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.25,1:01:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,distribute \Nover 5,000 publications \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.48,1:01:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and start an average \Nof 185 Bible studies. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.52,1:01:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,After some initial concern \Nfrom local authorities \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.39,1:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,over having literature carts \Nat the Golden Gate Bridge, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.23,1:01:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities have expressed appreciation \Nfor our brothers being there \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.26,1:01:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Bible’s message of hope. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.67,1:01:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been requested \Nthat we always have on hand \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.77,1:01:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the April 2014 Awake! \Nwith the cover title \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.51,1:01:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why Go On?\N—Three Reasons to Keep Living.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.54,1:01:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One afternoon an officer \Napproached a cart and said, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.78,1:01:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, your magazine worked!” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.91,1:01:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The police had just helped \Na young woman \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.55,1:01:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who was thinking \Nof jumping from the bridge. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.95,1:01:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When they reached her, \Nshe had the Awake! issue in her hand \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.32,1:01:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and had decided not to jump. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.03,1:01:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Life in this system \Ncan be difficult for everyone, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.77,1:02:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but our witnessing work \Ncomforts people\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.67,1:02:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and teaches them to know \Nand thank their Creator for life.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.07,1:02:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the longer we know Jehovah \Nas his Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.48,1:02:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the more reasons we find \Nto thank him for his acts of loyalty. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.88,1:02:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re even moved to sing \Nour appreciation to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.62,1:02:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like in this music video entitled \N“Our Thanks Go to You.”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.04,1:02:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When I cannot find\NAny peace of mind,\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.82,1:03:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You will listen.\NMy thanks go to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.83,1:03:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When troubles arise,\NWhatever the size,\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.45,1:03:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For your answers,\NOur thanks go to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.96,1:03:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We need not be anxious over anything.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.97,1:03:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll guard our hearts and our thoughts\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.98,1:03:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If we continue having trust in you to\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.22,1:04:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us peace of mind\NWhen life is unkind.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.33,1:04:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For our welfare,\NOur thanks go to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.15,1:04:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All the loyal \Nfind you loyal too.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.13,1:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For your care, \Nall our thanks go to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.88,1:05:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw the family in our music video \Nfacing economic pressure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.62,1:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and our dear older couple enduring \Nthe stress of failing health. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.49,1:05:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But as Philippians 4:6 encourages, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.22,1:05:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they let their “petitions \Nbe made known to God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.29,1:05:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I can do the same \Nfor any problem that causes us anxiety. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.50,1:05:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We should not only supplicate Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.60,1:05:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to give us his holy spirit \Nso that we can endure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.47,1:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but also thank him, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.54,1:05:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,fully assured \Nthat “he will not abandon his loyal ones.”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.91,1:05:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d again like to thank \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.91,1:05:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister Malenfant \Nfor being here with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.68,1:05:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,With almost 60 years \Nof full-time service, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.75,1:05:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Malenfants have so much \Nthey can share, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.78,1:05:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so we’re pleased to announce \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.79,1:05:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that an extended version \Nof their interview \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.85,1:05:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,will be released later this month \Non JW Broadcasting.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.39,1:05:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally in our program, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.49,1:05:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a special behind-the-scenes visit \Nwith the orchestra \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.53,1:05:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that records \Nour beautiful theocratic music.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.60,1:05:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In December 2015, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.07,1:05:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,75 musicians gathered \Nfrom 16 countries \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.67,1:06:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for a five-day session at our studio \Nin Patterson, New York. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.51,1:06:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A team of 15 technicians \Njoined them to record 22 pieces. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.95,1:06:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Among several songs \Nwe sing at our meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.75,1:06:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,was the stirring arrangement \Nof song 147, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.95,1:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“A Special Possession,” \Nthat we sang at this year’s Memorial.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.60,1:06:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The orchestra took time \Nfrom their busy session \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.44,1:06:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to send you \Ntheir Christian love and greetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.11,1:06:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thank them \Nand the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.91,1:06:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the music we have \Nto joyfully praise our God, Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.65,1:06:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re happy to have been together \Nwith you for this month’s program. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.52,1:06:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,From Brooklyn, New York, \Nthis is JW Broadcasting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.62,0:00:06.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,JW Broadcastingにようこそ！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.02,0:00:10.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のハイライトでは\N米国サンフランシスコの雑踏で行なう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.36,0:00:14.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別な公の証言を\N体験してみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:18.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,異なった言語を話す人のいる\Nこの区域で宣べ伝えている—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.27,0:00:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹の経験を聞きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:25.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人は 家族が\N霊的な活動をやめても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.28,0:00:27.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えつづけられるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.88,0:00:30.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族がショービジネスで忙しい中—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.68,0:00:32.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのようにエホバへの愛を成長させたか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.88,0:00:35.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹の経験を聞きましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:37.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,“結婚に備える”シリーズでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:41.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,交際中の人が\N生涯続く厳粛な約束をする前に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.69,0:00:46.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば“心の中の秘められた人”を\N知れるかを学びます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.66,0:00:51.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして忠節という素晴らしい\N特質についても考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.47,0:00:54.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,また60年以上\Nエホバに忠節に仕えてきた—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.80,0:00:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご夫婦のインタビューもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは2016年8月の\NJW Broadcastingです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:25.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のテーマは詩編 18:25の—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.67,0:01:28.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに対するダビデの歌から\Nとられています　\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:33.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,“忠節な者にはあなたは\N 忠節をもって行動する“とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.44,0:01:39.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,“忠節をもって行動する”という\N ヘブライ語は神の忠節な愛を連想させ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.42,0:01:46.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは誓約 忠誠 忠節 また深い愛着\Nによって動機づけられる愛のことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:52.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから忠節は単なる感情ではなく\N行動が伴い 愛に根ざしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:53.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが忠節な者に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:57.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛を込めて密着してくださるのを\N知るのは慰めです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.97,0:02:02.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしダビデはなぜ\N詩編 18:25を書いたのですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:07.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,表題を見るとこの詩編は\N“エホバが敵のたなごころより—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:11.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,“またサウルの手より\N 救い出してくださった”後に書かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.55,0:02:16.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの忠節な愛と強力な救いを\N経験したダビデが感じた—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.05,0:02:20.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びと安ど感について\N考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:22.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしダビデは生涯にわたりー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:26.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,最悪ともいえる不忠節な仕打ちを\N経験しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.60,0:02:31.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは王サウル 妻ミカル　\N信頼した助言者アヒトフェルー\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:33.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子アブサロムからのものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.60,0:02:40.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,最も信頼し愛した者たちの裏切りにより\Nダビデの心は深く傷つきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.68,0:02:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節は選べます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.08,0:02:46.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデの生涯を振り返ると\N何が分かりますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.38,0:02:49.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは神への忠節を選びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.85,0:02:52.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜な羊飼いの少年の時から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.32,0:02:55.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,国民を世話する\N勇敢な王となるまでずっと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.73,0:03:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデはエホバの心にかなう\N忠節な者であることを示しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:04.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし不公平に直面すると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:08.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に忠節を保つことは\N難しくなるものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:10.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデと勇敢な部下たちが\N味わった—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.97,0:03:13.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,切迫した状況を想像してください　\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,荒野に隠れ 蓄えもたびたび底を\N尽くほどでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:21.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,嫉妬にかられたサウル王の怒りに\N直面しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:25.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしサウルの命を奪うよう\N部下たちに促されたとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:28.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデはどんな選択をしましたか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.63,0:03:31.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,サムエル第一 24:6で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.19,0:03:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデが何と述べたか\N注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:37.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしが彼に向って手を出して—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:40.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしの主に\N エホバの油そそがれた者に—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:44.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,“このような事をするなど \Nわたしには エホバの見地からして—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:45.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“考えられないことだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼はエホバの油そそがれた者なのだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:53.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは自分が忠節であれば\Nエホバも自分に忠節であり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:57.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節な愛を示してくださることを\N知っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:00.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは個人的な感情を\N脇において—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.09,0:04:03.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの見地から\N物事を見るようにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.19,0:04:08.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,”忠節をもって行動”してくださるのを\N辛抱強く待ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:10.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,まもなく聖書の予告どおり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.37,0:04:13.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとその組織への\N忠節の試みとなる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.44,0:04:17.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生を一変させるほどの\N出来事に直面します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:20.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,今こそ忠節を強化するときです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.54,0:04:25.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら エホバがわたしたちの\N直面する不公正な状況をご存じであり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの忠節な奉仕に\N報いてくださることを確信できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:32.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう自問しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.82,0:04:35.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,“忠節のどんな行ないに基づいて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:38.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバはわたしに忠節を\N示してくださるだろうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.70,0:04:40.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:45.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,第一に エホバを擁護することによって\N忠節を示せます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:49.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは宇宙の主権者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.67,0:04:52.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように擁護できるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.11,0:04:55.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリフの立派な模範から学べます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:59.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリフはヨブと\N3人の偽りの慰め手が語る時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:01.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,辛抱強く耳を傾けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:04.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリフの反応に注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.55,0:05:07.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨブ 32:2，3\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.22,0:05:09.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ヨブに対して彼の怒りが燃え盛った”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:13.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ヨブが神よりも自分の魂を\N義と宣したことに対してであった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.90,0:05:15.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また その三人の友に対しても—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.70,0:05:17.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼の怒りは燃え盛った”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.63,0:05:19.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これは彼らが答えを見いださずー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“かえって神を邪悪な者と\Nしたからである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.41,0:05:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,義憤の火が\N若いエリフの中で燃えたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:33.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨブ 36:2, 3でエリフは\Nエホバを忠節に擁護してこう語りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.42,0:05:35.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしのことを辛抱するように”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:38.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしはあなたに告げ知らせよう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.05,0:05:41.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まだ 神のために\N 言うべき言葉があるということを”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは遠くから\N わたしの知識を携えて来てー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしを形作った方に\N 義を帰することにする”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:52.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エリフは神を賛美し\N擁護することによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気をもって忠節を示しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.47,0:06:00.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 なぜわたしたちも\Nエホバを擁護すべきですか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛ある天の父がさまざまな\N非難を受けているからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.45,0:06:06.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は三位一体の一部で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.55,0:06:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,地獄の火で人々を永遠に\N苦しめていると教えられています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:12.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,神はいないとか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:16.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,いたとしてもわたしたちのことなど\N気にかけていないというのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:19.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのようなうそは\Nサタン悪魔から出ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:24.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを擁護するために語り\Nサタンのうそを証明することによって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.97,0:06:27.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの忠節を示しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:33.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,全能の神が実在していることを\N大胆かつ熱心に宣明し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.11,0:06:38.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢明で義にかない愛のあるその方が\Nまもなく悪を終わらせ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:43.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節な者に永遠の命を\N与えることを知らせるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:46.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは石に叫ばせることも\Nできますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.36,0:06:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この特権をわたしたちに与えて\N忠節な者に誉れを与えておられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.73,0:06:56.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,第二に “忠実で思慮深い奴隷”である—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.90,0:07:01.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体に忠節を示すことで\Nエホバに忠節を示せます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:06.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとイエスは霊的な食物を与えるために\Nこの“奴隷”を用いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.58,0:07:09.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですからその奴隷に忠節を示すべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.91,0:07:14.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも“統治体も不完全な人間から\N成っている”と言うかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:16.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:19.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,地上で完全な生き方をしたのは\Nイエスだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球上には完全な人や組織は\N存在しません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.23,0:07:27.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年忠実だった兄弟は\Nよくこう言いました—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:31.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これは地上で最善の不完全な組織です”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.97,0:07:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,奴隷は間違いをしないと\Nイエスは言いませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.04,0:07:38.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠実で思慮深いと言われたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.27,0:07:42.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠実な奴隷にどのように聞き\Nまた従うかは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.01,0:07:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,神との友情の強さに\N直接影響を与えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.75,0:07:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 それは命を左右します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:56.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,では統治体がわたしたちの好まない\N霊的食物を提供したならどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:08:02.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,またある信条の説明がよく理解できず\N同意できない場合はどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:04.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 ペテロを含む\Nイエスの弟子たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:07.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい教えを示されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆の反応はどうでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.04,0:08:13.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 6:60をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.81,0:08:17.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,“弟子のうち大勢の者は\N これを聞いた際にー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:19.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“この話はひどい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.05,0:08:22.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,“だれがこれをきいていられようかと言った”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.32,0:08:23.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうなりましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.82,0:08:25.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,66節\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:29.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,“このために 弟子のうち多くの者が\N 後ろのものに戻って行きー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.96,0:08:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もはや彼と共に歩もうとはしなかった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.66,0:08:37.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし“あなたもつまずきましたか？”\Nとのイエスの問いに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.43,0:08:39.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロはどう反応しましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:42.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 6:68\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:44.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,“シモン・ペテロが彼に答えた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.21,0:08:47.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“主よ わたしたちは誰のところに\N 行けばよいというのでしょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.64,0:08:51.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたこそ永遠の命のことばを\N 持っておられます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.25,0:08:53.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい忠節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.72,0:08:59.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペテロの忠節はイエスがメシアであるとの\N確かな証拠に基づいていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.39,0:09:02.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,その忠節は信仰の証拠でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:07.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,それこそわたしたちが\N今日見倣いたい忠節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:11.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが物事を明確にされるのを\N待つ必要もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.63,0:09:15.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,その間 ペテロのような忠節を\N示せますように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.61,0:09:19.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして主イエスの足跡に\Nしっかりと従った—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.44,0:09:24.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠実な奴隷の指導にしっかりと\N付き従って行けますように\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.78,0:09:28.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,時々 個人的に必要な助言を\N受けることがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:31.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば\NJW Broadcastingでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:34.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体の成員からの愛ある諭しが\N与えられてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.96,0:09:38.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を許すこと 貴重なものをもって\Nエホバを敬うこと— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.69,0:09:42.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的に目覚めた状態を保つこと\Nなどについてです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.93,0:09:45.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ものみの塔」誌や集会では—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.07,0:09:50.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,服装や身づくろいに気を付けること\N良い仲間と健全な娯楽を選択すること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.67,0:09:54.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,また道徳的に清くあることなどについて\N教えられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:58.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに当てはめ\N必要な調整を図りますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.01,0:10:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとも自分の権利を\N主張しますか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:07.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒パウロは神権的な指示に対する\N忠節を試みられたことがありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.82,0:10:10.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒21章にある記録です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは宣教旅行から戻り\N西暦56年 エルサレムに到着しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:21.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神が諸国民の間で行なわれた\N 事柄について” 詳しく話したときの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.94,0:10:24.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロの喜びを想像できるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:28.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロの驚くべき経験について\N聞いたのち—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.04,0:10:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,年長者たちはパウロ個人が関係している\Nユダヤにおける問題を明らかにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒 21:21の記録を\N読んでみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:43.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし 彼ら［ユダヤ人の信者たち］は\N あなたについてー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.43,0:10:46.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたが諸国民の中にいる\N すべてのユダヤ人に対してー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.40,0:10:50.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,“モーセからの背教を説き\N 子供に割礼を施すこともー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.53,0:10:53.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“厳粛な習慣にしたがって\N 歩むこともしないように告げているー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“とのうわさを聞いています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:11:00.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロはおそらくこう思ったでしょう\N “自分が？ 背教？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.11,0:11:02.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうしてそんなことを言うのか?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:04.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“3回目の宣教旅行を\N 終えましたが—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.25,0:11:07.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバの祝福を見てください！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.02,0:11:11.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし年長者たちは\N使徒21:23, 24で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:15.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,おそらくパウロが予期していなかった\N明確な指示を与えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.49,0:11:18.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちが告げる\N このことをしてください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:22.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちのところには\N 誓約を立てた四人の人がいます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.13,0:11:23.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,“この人たちを連れて行ってー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.87,0:11:25.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,“一緒に儀式上の清めをしー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その費用の世話を見てー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.34,0:11:29.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,“彼らが頭をそってもらえるー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:30.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ようにしてやりなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:32.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,“こうすればだれもがー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:33.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたについて聞かされているー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:35.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“うわさには何の根拠もなくー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.95,0:11:37.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたが秩序正しく歩んでー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.48,0:11:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自らも律法を守っていることをー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.48,0:11:41.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“知るでしょう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.75,0:11:44.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロはその決定を\N疑問視したり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:47.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の権利を主張したり\Nすべきでしたか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:48.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは —\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.39,0:11:51.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,“律法はイエスと共に\N 杭につけられたという—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:54.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ガラテア人への手紙を\N 読まなかったのですか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.46,0:11:56.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは間違っていない—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:12:00.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,“少数の過敏な人のために\N なぜうわべを繕う必要があるのか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.90,0:12:02.81,Default2,,0,0,0,, と言うこともできました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:06.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし パウロは命の\N危険にもかかわらず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:09.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,求めに謙遜に応じました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:12.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは言わばプライドを\N飲み込みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.05,0:12:16.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の権利よりも大きな事が\N関係していることを知っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.85,0:12:20.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは他の人の良心に配慮しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:26.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,より重要なことはエホバと統治体に\N忠節を示したということです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.23,0:12:30.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,これよりも重要な事柄が\Nほかにあるでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.13,0:12:35.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロのように謙遜に 柔軟に\Nそして従順になるよう決意し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“忠実で思慮深い奴隷”に\N 忠実であることを示していきましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:48.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,第三として 長老たちに忠節であるなら\Nエホバに忠節でいられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:52.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと忠実な奴隷に\N忠節を示すことについて考えましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.96,0:12:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の長老たちから受ける\N指示についてはどうでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.36,0:13:01.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは毎週集会で\N長老たちの話や注解を聞き—　\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:04.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教で共に働き 交わります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.77,0:13:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,定期的に接する機会が増えると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:11.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,長老たちの不完全さや欠点が\N目に留まる機会も増えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:14.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの弱点に注目し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:19.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の取り決めに対する信頼を\N弱めてしまうことが生じ得ます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.05,0:13:23.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば雑誌に載っている写真を\N拡大してみると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.59,0:13:26.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,カラーの小さな点や画素が\N見えるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.96,0:13:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも遠くから見ると\Nきれいな写真や絵となります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.09,0:13:37.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様に長老たちを見るとき\N不完全さを拡大しないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.57,0:13:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さな点ではなく\N全体を見るようにしてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.27,0:13:48.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱心に働く愛ある牧者への忠節は\Nなぜそれほど重要ですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.34,0:13:53.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはこれら“人々の賜物”が\Nエホバの忠節な愛の表明であり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.38,0:13:58.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの貴重な羊を導き 養い \N保護してくれるからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.45,0:14:01.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,大患難が近い今\Nわたしたちの救いは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.72,0:14:07.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体の指示に従っている長老たちに\N進んで従うことにかかっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:12.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節は人にではなく\N不完全ながらも忠節な人々による—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:15.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの取り決めに対するものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはコラ ダタン アビラムが\N学ぶのを拒んだ教訓です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.34,0:14:25.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,民数記16章を扱った\N「エホバの権威に敬意を払う」という—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオの中で見られるコラの\N反抗的な態度に注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.61,0:14:58.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,コラとほかの者たちは\N神に忠節なふりをしていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:03.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが直接モーセとアロンを\N任命したことを無視していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:07.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,では実際にはだれに　\Nつぶやいていたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.79,0:15:11.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,民数記 26:9をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.59,0:15:14.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“このダタンとアビラムは\N 集会に呼ばれたものでー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:17.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“コラの集会に連なって\N モーセとアロンに対するー”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.67,0:15:19.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,“争いに加わった者たちである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そのさい彼らはエホバに対する\N 争いに加わったのである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:28.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセとその不完全さに\N注目する一方で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:33.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがイスラエル国民を\N導いておられることを見失ったのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.05,0:15:36.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際にはエホバと争っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.19,0:15:40.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の任命した人に対する\N不忠節の結果は死でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:44.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしコラの子たちは\N異なる決定をしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオクリップで父親とは\N全く異なる態度に注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはコラの子たちが示した\N忠節に動かされ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.87,0:16:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節に彼らの命を救われました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:02.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,見倣うべき立派な模範です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.30,0:17:06.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの民を導くよう\N今日任命されている人々に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:08.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,つぶやいたり不平を言ったりして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.58,0:17:12.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してエホバと争う者に\Nならないようにしたいものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.92,0:17:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠節に関する良い例や悪い例について\Nもっと知るためJW Broadcastingで\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.85,0:17:24.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバの権威に敬意を示す」のビデオ\N全体をご覧になるようお勧めします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.46,0:17:28.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに対する忠節をどのように\N示せるか振り返ってみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.80,0:17:33.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,第一にその方の証人として\Nエホバを擁護する\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.27,0:17:38.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,第二に“忠実で思慮深い奴隷”を\N忠節に支持し続ける\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:43.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,第三に任命された長老たちの指示に\N忠節に従う\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,コラの子たち ダビデ ペテロ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:48.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,またパウロなどの忠実な\N模範に倣うなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.55,0:17:51.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはエホバから\N忠節な人とみなされ—　\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:54.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの忠節な行ないを\N永遠に受けるに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ふさわしい人になることが\Nできるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.99,0:18:00.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,2番目の点は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:04.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠実で思慮深い奴隷の指示に\N従う方法を示していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:06.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体がどのように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:09.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,重要な決定に至るのか\N考えたことがありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.30,0:18:11.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルの朝の崇拝で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:15.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,デービッド・スプレーン兄弟が\N答えています \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:19.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,“次々と変化や変更があって\Nついていくのが大変だ” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.98,0:18:22.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなことをよく耳にします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.95,0:18:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 少し考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:29.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの変更は\Nどのように生じるのでしょうか \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:31.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体が水曜日の朝に集まって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.83,0:18:35.80,Default2,,0,0,0,, “さあ 今週はどんな変更を加えて\N兄弟たちを驚かせようか”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.80,0:18:38.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,などと話し合うのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.40,0:18:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは 忠実で思慮深いとは\Nいえません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.61,0:18:46.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,次々に変更が加えられる\Nように思えても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際には その決定に何年も費やされて\Nいることが少なくありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.35,0:19:01.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 現在の統治体が最初に\N取り組んだ大きな変更のひとつは— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.52,0:19:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国に支部委員会を置いて 機能させる\Nことができるかということでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.07,0:19:15.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年 それは難しいと\N考えられてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.74,0:19:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜなら米国には 統治体と世界本部の\N双方が置かれてきたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.31,0:19:25.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは大きな決定でしたし— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.88,0:19:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一日で決まるようなことでも\Nありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.19,0:19:36.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,円熟し 経験を積んだ兄弟たちの\N助言も必要でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.16,0:19:38.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 最終的には決定が下され—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:42.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはその決定を豊かに\N祝福してこられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:47.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは 支部委員会の熱心な\N働きと支えに感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らの支えを必要としています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:56.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の例も 幾つか取り上げましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.78,0:19:59.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,2009年1月の最初の週から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,神権宣教学校 奉仕会 そして\N書籍研究が一つになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.29,0:20:08.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,その決定には\N10年ほどが費やされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:15.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,1999年にはすでに そのことが\N話し合われていたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.16,0:20:19.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではなぜ そのときに決定が\N下されなかったのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:22.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は これらの集会を\N一つにまとめても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.91,0:20:26.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちが必要とする\N霊的食物を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:30.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,供給できるかどうかを確かめたいと\N思っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:34.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある水曜日のこと\N確か3時半ごろだったと思いますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,会議が長引いているところに —\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:40.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,二つの大きな支部から\N手紙が届きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:45.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの支部によれば \N七つか八つの書籍研究があるのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.53,0:20:50.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,長老と奉仕の僕が一人ずつしか\Nいないような大きな会衆が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:51.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つもあって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.77,0:20:57.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,長老が五つ 奉仕の僕が三つ\Nという具合に書籍研究を司会し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.37,0:21:00.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,その上で他の集会の準備も\N行なっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:06.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらの兄弟たちは 書籍研究の司会と\N集会の準備で精一杯でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.75,0:21:09.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の支部から受け取った\N手紙には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.65,0:21:14.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,書籍研究の出席者が減っている\N理由が書かれていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:17.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,手紙によると 奉仕者たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,書籍研究を含め すべての集会を\N大切にしているものの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:27.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,あまりの貧しさゆえに 週日の\N二つの集会にバスで行く費用を賄えず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:31.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,どちらかを選ばなければならない\Nとのことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:33.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校と奉仕会の集会に出れば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:36.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な指導を2時間受けられるのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.31,0:21:39.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,書籍研究では1時間です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:40.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 多くの場合—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.22,0:21:44.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校と奉仕会の集会が選ばれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.39,0:21:46.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,これら二通の手紙は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.46,0:21:50.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが\N兄弟たちの実情を理解し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.23,0:21:54.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,決定を下すうえで\N助けとなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:56.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,さて 2008年から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.23,0:22:00.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般用と研究用の「ものみの塔」誌が\N発行されるようになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この決定にも\N長い時間がかかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:07.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,何度も話し合いましたが— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.24,0:22:10.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,”性急にならず \N 少し待ってみよう—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.18,0:22:14.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバは何を望まれるだろうか？”\N と考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.02,0:22:17.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切なのは \Nエホバが何を望まれるか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.15,0:22:20.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを どのように見極めるか？\Nということでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.36,0:22:23.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ”羊毛の試み”を\Nすることにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.76,0:22:27.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,2006年に「目ざめよ！」誌を\N月1回の発行とし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.43,0:22:31.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ものみの塔」誌は\N引き続き月2回の発行としました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.23,0:22:36.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,月に4冊ではなく 3冊の雑誌が\N発行されるようにしたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.54,0:22:37.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.61,0:22:41.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,“一年間試して 雑誌の配布が\N急激に落ち込むようだったら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:43.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,“エホバの支持はなかったと考えて—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“「目ざめよ！」誌を月2回の\N 発行に戻そう”と考えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.38,0:22:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,結果はどうでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.09,0:22:57.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,前年に 月4冊発行されていたとき\Nと同じくらいの配布が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.09,0:23:00.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,月3冊でも\Nみられたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.10,0:23:02.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで エホバが\N新たな取り決めを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.13,0:23:05.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,支持してくださっていることが\Nわかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.40,0:23:11.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんも 兄弟たちに直接的に\N語りかける研究用と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.01,0:23:16.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,一般の人たちの必要に合わせた\N一般用の両方の備えに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.78,0:23:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,感謝しておられるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.68,0:23:26.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国の業に影響を及ぼす\Nどんな決定を下すときにも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.05,0:23:30.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は 霊的な面でもたらされる\N結果を考慮します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.43,0:23:38.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 2008年に公開講演の長さが\N45分から30分へと変更になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.80,0:23:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この決定は 兄弟たちにどんな\N霊的な影響を与えたでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.21,0:23:49.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし皆さんが 長老の大勢いる\N都市部の会衆にいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.81,0:23:53.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,近隣の会衆にも\N長老が大勢いる場合—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.18,0:23:57.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,この調整の意図が\N分かりにくいかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.12,0:24:00.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 統治体は物事の\N全体を見ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.89,0:24:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢の兄弟たちが必要の大きな会衆で\N働いていて 外国語を学んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.00,0:24:11.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした会衆の多くでは\N長老たちも言語を学習中です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.77,0:24:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある兄弟たちは 公開講演を1分準備する\Nのに1時間かかると言っていました \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.11,0:24:22.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ということは \N45分の公開講演の準備に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.68,0:24:26.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,合計45時間を費やす\Nことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.55,0:24:29.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから講演の長さを \N短くするなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.78,0:24:34.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの会衆でより多くの\N公開講演を提供できるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.52,0:24:38.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに 孤立した会衆で\N奉仕する長老もいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.76,0:24:42.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣の会衆まで100キロ以上も\N離れている場合があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.63,0:24:44.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある会衆に\N一人の長老がいて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.83,0:24:49.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,100キロほど先の会衆に別の長老が\N一人いるという具合です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:51.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの兄弟たちが\N協力し合っても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.54,0:24:55.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,45分なら どれほどの公開講演を\N提供できるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.64,0:24:59.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,15分の短縮が \N違いをもたらします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.95,0:25:03.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし視野が狭く\N自分の置かれている状況や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.69,0:25:07.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の会衆のことしか\N考慮に入れないとすれば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.22,0:25:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,特定の決定が下された理由が\N分かりにくいかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.66,0:25:15.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,このことは教義の解明にも\Nあてはまります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.83,0:25:20.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は 集まりあって 聖書に\Nついて討議するのが大好きです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.74,0:25:24.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を取り出し それぞれが\N調査した事柄を持ち寄り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.81,0:25:30.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖句について調べ 分析しはじめると\N兄弟たちには笑顔があふれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.45,0:25:34.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,霊的な事柄を話し合うことを\N愛しているからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.95,0:25:40.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 新たな解明が示されるときには\N長い時間がかけられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.52,0:25:42.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.09,0:25:47.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,一つの聖句の解明はドミノのように \N他の箇所にも影響を及ぼすからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.96,0:25:52.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,新たな解明が他の預言に影響を\N及ぼすこともあるので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.53,0:25:57.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,関係するすべての要素が\N調和しているという確信が必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:02.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,このように 次々に\N変更が発表されるとしても\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.04,0:26:06.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらは 注意深く\N考え抜かれているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.85,0:26:08.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.45,0:26:13.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジャラズ兄弟やバー兄弟のような\N統治体の年長の成員は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.22,0:26:18.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い成員と同じほど 変化を生み出す\Nことに関心を持っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:22.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは 非常に進歩的でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.30,0:26:26.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,忠実で思慮深い奴隷の愛ある気遣いを\N感じさせるコメントです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.84,0:26:29.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体が行なっている\N事柄を聞いて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.37,0:26:32.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,その指示に一層従いたいと\N思いましたか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.54,0:26:35.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は\N経験ある兄弟たちに相談し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.34,0:26:38.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の兄弟たちの\N異なる状況を考え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.58,0:26:40.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,最も重要なこととして—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.25,0:26:43.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,辛抱強く祈りのうちに\Nエホバのご意志を知り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.62,0:26:47.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分たちの決定の上に\N祝福を求めているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.96,0:26:50.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中の兄弟姉妹たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.09,0:26:52.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと組織に忠節を\N示すことからくる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.49,0:26:55.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,祝福を詳しく\N話すことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.96,0:27:00.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日ここにそのようなお二人を\Nお招きしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.54,0:27:04.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ウィリアム・マレンフォント兄弟と\N妻のサンドラ姉妹です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.31,0:27:07.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,マレンフォント兄弟は\N教育委員会の援助者で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.21,0:27:11.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,マレンフォント姉妹は現在\N奉仕部門で働いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.25,0:27:15.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人のすばらしい霊的な\N歩みについて伺いましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.75,0:27:19.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,スタジオにお越しいただき\Nうれしく思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.32,0:27:23.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人をさらに知ることができる\Nのを楽しみにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.63,0:27:25.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,過去にさかのぼって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.29,0:27:28.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年にわたるエホバへの\N忠実で忠節な奉仕の道を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.83,0:27:31.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように\N歩み始められましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.47,0:27:33.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,1954年のことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.64,0:27:37.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,母は数年間 時々エホバの証人と\N連絡をとっていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.84,0:27:39.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが20歳のころです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.81,0:27:43.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,母はカリフォルニア州\Nオークランド・セントラル会衆の—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.38,0:27:45.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,公開講演に招待されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.68,0:27:50.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に来るかと尋ねられ\N“うん 行くよ”と答えました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.12,0:27:53.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,その集会に高校のころからの\N知り合いがいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.89,0:27:58.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,あとから近づいてきて\N聖書研究が必要だと言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.43,0:28:00.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,乗り気ではなかったんですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.43,0:28:02.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,強く勧められたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.16,0:28:04.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,“じゃあ来ていいよ”と言ったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.80,0:28:07.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神を真とすべし」の本で研究が始まり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.74,0:28:10.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,4か月後にバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.17,0:28:13.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそまさに自分が\N求めていたものだったのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.48,0:28:15.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,気づかなかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.94,0:28:17.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い選択ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.55,0:28:20.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンドラ姉妹の\Nスタートはいかがですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.85,0:28:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしが生まれる前\N両親は真理を探していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.12,0:28:28.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,幼い娘を亡くしたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:32.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,慰めを求めに\N幾つもの教会に行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.36,0:28:35.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 聖職者は\N何の慰めにもならず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.56,0:28:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神は天使をもう一人望まれたのですよ”と\N言うだけでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.17,0:28:42.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は怒って\N“そんなはずはない！”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.74,0:28:46.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もし必要なら神は造ることが\N おできになる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.04,0:28:49.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,“娘を取り去るはずはない！”\Nと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.54,0:28:52.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある晩 両親は\Nラジオを聞いていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.45,0:28:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこでエホバの証人の話を聞きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.79,0:29:00.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,その題は「死者はどこにいるか」でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.56,0:29:02.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,想像してみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.62,0:29:07.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,死者の状態 復活の希望について\Nすべて聖書から証明したんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.96,0:29:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,父はすぐに \N「これこそ真理だ！」と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.07,0:29:17.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでラジオ局に手紙を書き\N話の小冊子を手に入れ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.71,0:29:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ものみの塔」誌の\N予約購読を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.48,0:29:25.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもわたしが生まれて\N3歳になった時に初めて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.68,0:29:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある証人の家族に会えたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.02,0:29:30.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,全時間奉仕を選び—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.45,0:29:35.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生をエホバに捧げるきっかけと\Nなったものは何でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.42,0:29:39.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,56年の大会に出席したことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.13,0:29:41.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,54年にバプテスマを受け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.13,0:29:45.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,56年のカリフォルニア州\Nオールバニーの地域大会に行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.70,0:29:48.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこに開拓者ブースがあったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.87,0:29:52.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブースに近づくと\N年長の姉妹がわたしを見て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.51,0:29:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたは若くて強いのに\N なぜ開拓者でないの？”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.31,0:30:02.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そうだ なぜだろう?”と思い\N1956年に開拓を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.45,0:30:04.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それがきっかけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.09,0:30:08.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返ると これは\N人生の最善の決定でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.16,0:30:12.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンドラ姉妹のきっかけは\N何でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.46,0:30:15.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓奉仕を行なうのは\N当然のことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.80,0:30:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人はそう\N励まされていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.33,0:30:22.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどの若者が\Nそうしていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.04,0:30:26.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,1, 2年後結婚して\N家族を持つかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.01,0:30:28.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも開拓奉仕の年月は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:33.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,残りの人生で忠実な奉仕をするための\N素晴らしい土台となるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.55,0:30:35.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.25,0:30:39.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓をして どのようにお二人は\N出会ったんでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.32,0:30:44.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,1956年 カリフォルニア州\Nオークランドでの巡回大会で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.73,0:30:47.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても興味深いことが起きたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.86,0:30:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはステージを解体していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.33,0:30:54.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ステージから大きなベニヤ板を\N運んでいると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.50,0:30:57.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンドラにぶつかって\N倒してしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.51,0:31:01.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,“いい自己紹介の仕方ではないな”と\N 思いながらも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.28,0:31:03.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,この機会を利用して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.08,0:31:08.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ところで 友人との集いに\N 一緒に来ませんか？”と言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.18,0:31:09.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,良かったですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.25,0:31:11.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ そして\N言ったとおりにしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.85,0:31:15.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさん交わり\N数カ月後 結婚しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.52,0:31:19.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人とも開拓奉仕をして\Nエホバに仕え とても幸福でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.96,0:31:22.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は兄弟に惚れたんですね？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.23,0:31:23.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.20,0:31:25.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,良かったですね！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.03,0:31:28.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚してすぐ \N指示に応じられたと聞いております\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.70,0:31:32.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ええ 結婚してまだ1か月ほど\Nだったと思いますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.54,0:31:35.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,—巡回訪問がありました\N—そうね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.91,0:31:41.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,組織は 特別開拓者としてどこでも\N特にアメリカの必要の大きな場所で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.52,0:31:45.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜んで奉仕する開拓者を\N探しているとのことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.95,0:31:49.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もちろん 喜んでそうします”\Nと言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.92,0:31:53.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚して4か月後\Nアイオワ州ディコーラで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.33,0:31:57.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別開拓者として奉仕する\N割り当てを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.77,0:32:02.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆に8人の伝道者しかいない\Nとても興味深い場所です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.74,0:32:06.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,到着して王国会館での\N集会から始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.34,0:32:10.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館はディコーラ中心部にある\Nハント雑貨店の上にあり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.95,0:32:14.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちはその裏の部屋に\N住んでいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.92,0:32:17.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,周りに大勢の兄弟がおらず—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.52,0:32:22.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分でなんとかしていると\N励ましと仲間が欲しくなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.02,0:32:26.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでアイオワ州\Nストロベリー・ポイントまで行っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.29,0:32:29.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこにチャールズ・シナツコ\Nとシャーリーが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.03,0:32:31.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,ワンルームの丸太小屋に\N住んでいたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.67,0:32:34.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,励まし合うためによく行きましたよ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.20,0:32:37.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,その頃の丸太小屋での\N素敵な写真です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.14,0:32:39.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,業に忙しくしておられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.51,0:32:42.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな特別な招待を\N受けられましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.91,0:32:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,第34期ギレアデ学校への\N招待を受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.25,0:32:53.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,アイオワ州で2年半特別開拓奉仕を\Nしたあとの素晴らしい出来事です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.92,0:32:58.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,レバノンが任地でしたが\Nビザを取得できず入れませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.66,0:33:00.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで組織から—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.29,0:33:04.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,“モロッコでの割り当てを受け入れますか？”\Nと尋ねられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.40,0:33:06.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこにでも行くつもりでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.40,0:33:08.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでニューヨーク市から船に乗り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.84,0:33:13.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,5日かけて大西洋を横断し\Nカサブランカに到着しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.27,0:33:14.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.58,0:33:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,モロッコでの宣教者奉仕は\Nいかがでしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.35,0:33:22.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても興味深く\N本当に楽しみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.48,0:33:27.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語しか話せなかったので\Nフランス語を学ぶ必要がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.66,0:33:30.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,モロッコでの宣教奉仕の最初の月—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.19,0:33:35.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,30日の間 一日11時間\N言語を勉強しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.53,0:33:38.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても疲れるので\Nフランス映画を見に行き—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.83,0:33:42.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時間も言語の時間に\N数えたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.14,0:33:44.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから タンジールに移動しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.97,0:33:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこにはスペイン語会衆があり\Nスペイン語も勉強しなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.45,0:33:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも その文化に触れ 奉仕できたのは\N本当に大きな祝福でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.02,0:34:00.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,4年後 家族に会うために\N帰国されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.92,0:34:04.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後 どんな試練となる\N出来事があったでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.73,0:34:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その点はサンドラが話します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.30,0:34:12.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,通常4年間任地にいると\N休暇をとって帰省し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.80,0:34:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族に会うことができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.90,0:34:18.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰国して 家族に会いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.54,0:34:19.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康診断を受けると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.97,0:34:23.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,深刻な健康上の問題を抱えている\Nことがわかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.78,0:34:27.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 費用をまかなえるだけの\N蓄えはありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.15,0:34:31.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでビルが協会に手紙を書き\N取り決めが設けられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.72,0:34:34.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まず状況に対処してください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.06,0:34:37.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,“元気になったら連絡してください”\Nと言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.33,0:34:42.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ビルは医療上の必要と\N生活のために仕事を見つけました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.23,0:34:46.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 本当に自分たちは\N駄目な人間だと感じたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.60,0:34:51.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはわたしたちが落胆し\N動揺していることをご存知でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.91,0:34:56.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,何が必要か知っておられ\Nそれを与えてくださったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.58,0:34:59.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,体調が良くなり\N時間に余裕が出てきたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.58,0:35:01.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓を始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.62,0:35:04.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは宣教を\N祝福してくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.69,0:35:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,信じられないほどにです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.52,0:35:10.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,“産出的ではない”と\N思われていた区域で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.12,0:35:13.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,25人も集会に出席した\Nことがあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.36,0:35:17.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,その多くがバプテスマを受け\N今でも良い友人です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.17,0:35:18.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,すごいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.43,0:35:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは必要をご存知で\N備えてくださるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.57,0:35:23.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.34,0:35:25.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰国して困難に対処する間—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.74,0:35:29.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな誘惑を退ける必要が\Nあったでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.08,0:35:35.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは健康上の理由で戻る兄弟姉妹の\N多くが直面する誘惑だと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.82,0:35:39.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況ゆえに落ち着く\N兄弟たちもおられますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.05,0:35:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,誘惑となるのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.42,0:35:41.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,“家に帰ってきた”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.82,0:35:44.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,“もう何年もモロッコで奉仕した”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.33,0:35:46.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“全時間宣教を行なった”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.29,0:35:50.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,“今は落ち着こう 家を買おう”\Nと考えることです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.73,0:35:54.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそれはわたしたちの\N願いではありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.17,0:36:00.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,サンドラの体調が良くなると\Nすぐ開拓を始め 本部に手紙を書きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.14,0:36:03.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ここにわたしたちがおります\N 何でも果たせます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.38,0:36:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,“何ができるでしょうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.61,0:36:07.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,よい模範ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.38,0:36:11.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,組織で自分を役立たせ\N次はどこに遣わされたのでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.79,0:36:13.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい割り当てです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.89,0:36:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別開拓者として\NワシントンDCに遣わされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.83,0:36:20.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,スペイン語会衆の設立を手伝うためです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:23.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に豊かな祝福となりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.80,0:36:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこにいた1年半で\N小さな会衆が設立されたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.24,0:36:33.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,別の祝福も受け\N巡回奉仕に割り当てられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.34,0:36:36.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,フロリダ州のキー･ウエストから\Nオルランドまでの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:39.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,アメリカで一つの\Nスペイン語巡回区です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.41,0:36:43.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,それからニューヨーク市に来て\Nブロンクスに住みました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.68,0:36:47.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回区を持ち スペイン語の\N野外で地域奉仕をしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.89,0:36:50.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから テキサス州の谷と呼ばれる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:55.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,テキサス州リオグランデ･バレーの\N巡回区で数年奉仕しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.33,0:36:58.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,その次は テキサス州\Nヒューストンから—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.10,0:37:02.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,カリフォルニア州ユバシティまでの\Nスペイン語地域区です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.30,0:37:04.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,心から楽しみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.14,0:37:06.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさに旅行する奉仕ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.61,0:37:10.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,1977年に別の招待を受けられました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.38,0:37:12.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのとおりです！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.21,0:37:17.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,レイマート大会ホールでロサンゼルスの\N地域大会の準備をしていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.29,0:37:21.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,すると ベテルへの招待の手紙を\N受け取ったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.29,0:37:26.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ベテルに招待されるのは\N本当に 本当に特別な特権です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.23,0:37:30.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時 大勢の旅行する監督が\N奉仕部門に入り働いていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.93,0:37:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしも奉仕部門に入り\Nサンドラはハウスキーパーになりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.04,0:37:38.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,二人ともベテルに来て喜びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.87,0:37:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,まあ そうね...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.14,0:37:45.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは宣教を本当に愛していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.71,0:37:49.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に 地域奉仕で毎週 \N巡回監督やその妻と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.42,0:37:52.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に奉仕するのが\N好きだったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.05,0:37:57.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ベテルでの奉仕を切望していた\Nというわけではありませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.46,0:38:01.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバは今回も\N必要なことをご存知だったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.90,0:38:05.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここに来て ベテルでの生活に\N慣れ始めると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.37,0:38:09.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,これがいかに大きな祝福か\Nということがわかりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.24,0:38:14.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんのエホバの忠実な証人と\N親しい交わりを持てたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.71,0:38:16.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかにもたくさんあると\N思いますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.91,0:38:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つか話してくださり\Nありがとうございます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.82,0:38:26.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体はベテルと野外の業に\N大きな調整を行ない—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.09,0:38:30.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの長年の忠実で忠節な兄弟たち—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.29,0:38:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,旅行する兄弟たちや会衆の監督\Nベテルの監督に影響がありました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.13,0:38:43.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体が最近行なった変更について\Nどうお感じですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.34,0:38:46.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても賢明な決定だと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.14,0:38:48.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体は何が必要か\N知っており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.71,0:38:52.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,長年奉仕した年長の男子に\N感謝しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.48,0:38:55.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,巡回奉仕や地域奉仕\Nあるいはどこであれ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.85,0:39:00.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,業に自分を費やしてきた兄弟たちは\N“二倍の誉れに値”します\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.96,0:39:03.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも より若い人たちが来て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.52,0:39:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,責任を担うべき時が来ることも\N認めなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.00,0:39:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際 わたしたちが若かった頃は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.56,0:39:14.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんの少しの背景と訓練で\N責任を担っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.47,0:39:20.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は王国福音宣明者のための学校や\N王国宣教学校があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.51,0:39:24.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,若い人が訓練を受ける\N多くの機会があるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.25,0:39:27.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで素晴らしい取り決めだと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.48,0:39:30.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,大勢の若い男子は\Nとてもよくやっており—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.25,0:39:32.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,責任を担う準備ができています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.85,0:39:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,組織全体にとっての祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.06,0:39:37.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.59,0:39:40.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの兄弟たちが益を受けます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.59,0:39:41.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人について—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.73,0:39:46.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,また賢明な決定を下してきた\N兄弟姉妹について知ることができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.47,0:39:50.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,60年以上に及ぶ忠実で忠節な\N奉仕を振り返りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.87,0:39:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,人生の決定に\N後悔がおありでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.14,0:39:58.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,全くありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.75,0:40:01.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,あきらめたことや行ったことは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.42,0:40:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,みなエホバへのプレゼントと考えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.19,0:40:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ少女だった頃 農場に出て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.12,0:40:13.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に満月の時には\Nエホバに祈りこう言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.33,0:40:17.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしの人生すべてを\Nあなたの奉仕に用いてください”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.90,0:40:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは祈りに答えてくださり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.07,0:40:21.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは人生の大半を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.94,0:40:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕に\N費やすことができました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.27,0:40:26.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,素敵ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.51,0:40:30.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟は歩みにおける犠牲を\Nどう見ておられますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.48,0:40:35.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に仕えるためにあきらめたことは\N犠牲と言えるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.52,0:40:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに差し出すものも犠牲と言えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.62,0:40:41.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデが詩編54編で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.29,0:40:47.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは自ら進んで\Nあなたに犠牲をささげます”\Nと述べているようにです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.23,0:40:50.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしは犠牲をそのように見ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.63,0:40:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ神にお仕えするために\N自分自身を喜んで差し出しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.00,0:41:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて サンドラは\N素晴らしいパートナーです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.21,0:41:02.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,好きな聖句はたくさんありますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.31,0:41:07.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,特にいつも思いの中にあるのは\Nローマ 14:7, 8です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.52,0:41:10.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちは 生きるなら\Nエホバに対して生き—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.75,0:41:14.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“死ぬならエホバに対して死ぬのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.02,0:41:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それゆえ 生きるにしても死ぬにしても\Nわたしたちはエホバのものです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.06,0:41:22.80,Default2,,0,0,0,, そのような決定をしてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.80,0:41:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者だからというだけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.90,0:41:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違いなく考えうる最良の人生を\N歩んできました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.07,0:41:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを第一にしてきた人生に\N後悔はまったくありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.78,0:41:44.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,お二人からお聞きできたのは\N本当に特権です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.29,0:41:49.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,60年以上の忠実なエホバへの奉仕ですから\N話は尽きないことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.36,0:41:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,貴重な洞察と宝石のような経験を\N語ってくださりありがとうございました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.46,0:41:58.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,マレンフォント夫妻と同様\N多くの証人たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.67,0:42:02.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,大人になるまで聖書の真理を\N教えてもらえませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.67,0:42:05.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある若者たちは\N真理の種が植えられたものの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.91,0:42:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の状況ゆえに\N何年も芽が出ない状態でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.18,0:42:14.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリー・ウェルズ姉妹は\N家族の特殊な才能の故に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.01,0:42:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,命の道になかなか乗り出せなかった\Nことを説明しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.16,0:42:24.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初にロデオを披露したのは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.33,0:42:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,8歳の時です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.90,0:42:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは一，二を争う\Nロデオチームでした \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.41,0:42:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の強みは恐れを\N感じないことでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.68,0:42:52.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,まあ 楽しい日々でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.45,0:42:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,旅行も楽しかったですし—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.46,0:42:58.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族一緒でしたから\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.36,0:43:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 虚しかったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.37,0:43:09.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,走っている馬の上で \N体操するようなものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.07,0:43:13.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもそばに馬がいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.11,0:43:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は馬の調教のプロでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.14,0:43:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一日中 山の中で馬に乗ったものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.72,0:43:28.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,夕方家に帰ってから\N曲乗りを練習しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.39,0:43:31.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,本で曲乗りを学びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.49,0:43:36.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,絵を見ながら やり方を学んだので\N試行錯誤の連続でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.73,0:43:41.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが学ぶと同時に\N馬も学んでいきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.30,0:43:45.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,私がやりたいことを\Nなんでもさせてくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.11,0:43:48.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,名前はスウィートリップスです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.08,0:43:52.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,8歳の時に飼うようになって\N自分で名前を付けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.15,0:43:55.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の親友でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.62,0:43:59.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,両親はロデオ競技に\N活発に参加していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.62,0:44:01.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,母はバレル・レーシング—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.82,0:44:04.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,父はサドル・ブロンコ・ライダーでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.93,0:44:08.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はエホバの証人として育ちました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.80,0:44:12.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも6歳か7歳くらいの時に—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.20,0:44:15.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,父が真理から\N離れてしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.80,0:44:17.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直に言うと—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.50,0:44:19.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,王国会館で発表があったとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.97,0:44:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういう意味か分かりませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.21,0:44:24.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな泣いていたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.98,0:44:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,私も泣きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.01,0:44:29.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも分かっていませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.72,0:44:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,このころから家族は\N不活発になってしまいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.52,0:44:38.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,旅行しながら大きくなりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.13,0:44:40.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,次から次へとロデオを回り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.39,0:44:43.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,国中をくまなく旅行しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.03,0:44:46.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,当初 きょうだいでロデオをしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.37,0:44:50.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,コニー ケリー 私 ジムです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.04,0:44:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族全員で旅行できていたので\N幸せでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.71,0:45:01.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,猛スピードでの技や難しい芸に\Nあえて挑戦する私たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.82,0:45:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あまりに周りとかけ離れていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.99,0:45:08.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,お客さんはすごく喜びました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.92,0:45:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎年、同じ会場に呼ばれたものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.49,0:45:15.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな生活でしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.66,0:45:18.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,記念式は一度も欠かしませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.53,0:45:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心のどこかでそうしなければと\N思っていたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.24,0:45:26.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さいときは分かっていませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.21,0:45:30.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,両親は真理を心に\N植え付けてくれていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.51,0:45:34.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖母がわたしと真理との架け橋でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.38,0:45:37.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,牧場に住んでいた祖母を訪ねると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.42,0:45:43.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,忙しくても 毎日必ず勉強していたのが\N印象的でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.02,0:45:47.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を読んで\N雑誌を深く研究していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.36,0:45:49.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖母のその姿を見て—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.43,0:45:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の中で徐々に真理の種が\N育ち始めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.87,0:45:57.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,導きがほしいと思いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.81,0:46:00.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,砂の上に描いた線のように—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.41,0:46:03.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,どちらに行くべきか迷っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.88,0:46:06.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,皮肉にも 最初に手に取ったのが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.65,0:46:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.75,0:46:13.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 3:5，6に感動しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.45,0:46:16.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,“心をつくしてエホバに依り頼め” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.82,0:46:19.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自分の理解に頼ってはならない” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.73,0:46:23.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたのすべての道において\N 神を認めよ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.56,0:46:25.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そうすれば神ご自身が—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.63,0:46:28.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの道筋を\N まっすぐにしてくださる” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.74,0:46:33.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,この言葉通りに生きたいと\N強く願ったものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.67,0:46:37.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,年に10か月はロデオを周っていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.28,0:46:39.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,地域大会には行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.68,0:46:43.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,「永遠に生きる」の本が\Nちょうどいい時に発表されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.95,0:46:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,変化しなければと\N思っている時だったんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.82,0:46:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,研究が始まり\N自分でも聖書を読み—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.76,0:46:56.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,勉強するようになって\Nエホバが現実の存在になりました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.83,0:46:59.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人が活発になると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.03,0:47:01.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族みんながそれに続きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.77,0:47:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,父も真理に戻ってきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.64,0:47:10.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,ロデオで私たちの生活は\N成り立っていましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.01,0:47:13.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう終わりにしようと\N家族で決めました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.38,0:47:15.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはつまり\Nこれまでのすべてを— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.85,0:47:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,手離すということでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.02,0:47:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い返すと，馬を売る時が\N一番つらかったです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.69,0:47:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちには強い絆があって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.00,0:47:33.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば一心同体でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.73,0:47:36.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 揺らぎませんでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.57,0:47:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で決めた道でしたから\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.01,0:47:44.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,85年の10月に\Nバプテスマを受けました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.18,0:47:47.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後のロデオは86年の2月で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.55,0:47:50.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで契約がすべて終了しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.68,0:47:53.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,86年9月に開拓奉仕をはじめ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.95,0:47:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それ以来ずっと続けています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.26,0:48:00.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを愛する兄弟と結婚しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.59,0:48:05.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,国際建設で夫婦一緒に\N奉仕する機会に恵まれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.17,0:48:08.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,メキシコで働き\Nベネズエラでも奉仕しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.67,0:48:09.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は長老で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.84,0:48:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,母は開拓者です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.57,0:48:14.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,きょうだい全員が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.27,0:48:17.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,一度は開拓奉仕を楽しみました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.18,0:48:21.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,今は巡回奉仕を行なっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.88,0:48:26.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒にエホバに仕えるのは\Nすばらしい祝福です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.39,0:48:28.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎日何をしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.02,0:48:30.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのためにしているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.92,0:48:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これこそが私のしたかったことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.03,0:48:38.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,若いときに別の道を歩んでいたら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.87,0:48:42.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,今頃は生きていなかったかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.77,0:48:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれは本当に危険でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.41,0:48:48.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,名声も成功も虚しいだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.88,0:48:50.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の命を—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.51,0:48:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕えることを望んでいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.15,0:48:57.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,後悔はありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.78,0:48:59.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの奉仕で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.25,0:49:02.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうしておけばよかったと\N思うことはありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.49,0:49:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,もっと仕えたい それだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.70,0:49:13.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリーと家族にとっては\Nロデオの仕事よりも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.83,0:49:17.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの忠節を選ぶには\N勇気が求められました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.37,0:49:20.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,好きな活動や仕事が\N献身にどう影響するかを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.61,0:49:25.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りのうちに決定するなら\Nエホバはいつも助けてくださいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.18,0:49:30.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,費やす時間や潜んでいる危険は\N魂を込めた奉仕を妨げるでしょうか？ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.22,0:49:34.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの忠節は\N人生の重要な決定を下す際—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.22,0:49:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則にどのように\N従うかによって示せます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.09,0:49:43.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚相手として誰を選ぶかは\N非常に重要な決定の一つです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.43,0:49:49.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“結婚に備える”シリーズのパート１が\N2016年5月で紹介されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.64,0:49:54.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのドラマでは 結婚するには\Nまだ早すぎることを理解した姉妹が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.34,0:50:00.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,今クリスチャンの特質を培うなら\N将来の結婚に役立つことを悟りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.35,0:50:03.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,パート2では交際期間中の二人が—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.32,0:50:06.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように“心の中の\N秘められた人”を見極め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.69,0:50:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,配偶者とエホバに忠節な結婚相手を\N見出せるかを描いています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.21,0:50:36.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジミンとの出会いは\N思いがけないものでした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.98,0:50:39.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,交際相手を探しては\Nいませんでしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.92,0:50:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼女と話すとすべてが\Nしっくりきたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.99,0:50:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,唯一の問題は距離です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.29,0:51:20.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,飛行機で一度\N会いに行きましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.99,0:51:24.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほとんどはオンラインで\Nコミュニケーションを取るだけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.93,0:51:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼女だ！と\Nどうすればわかるのだろう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.20,0:51:35.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,父に相談するのが\N最善だと判断しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.34,0:51:39.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は 交際が一層真剣に\Nなっていること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.45,0:51:43.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてわたしの心配も\N理解してくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.52,0:51:45.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.55,0:51:48.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,“大切なことは変わらないよ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.02,0:51:53.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,“相手が隣に住んでいようと\N 地球の裏側に住んでいようとね”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.13,0:51:57.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,“見た目や社会的な地位しか\N 見ない人は多いけれど—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.16,0:52:00.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,“本当に成功するために\N 必要なものは—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.23,0:52:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“霊性なんだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.18,0:52:15.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジミンの長老たちとも話し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.68,0:52:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,素晴らしい開拓者だと\N言っていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.02,0:52:21.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,父から\N”良かったね”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.52,0:52:25.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“でも さらに「心の中の\N 秘められた人」を知るには—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.43,0:52:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“時間がかかるんだ”\N と言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.57,0:52:43.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも“心の中の秘められた人”を\N知るにはどうすればよいのだろう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.71,0:52:46.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,“まず 祈ること”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.58,0:52:49.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ジミンの本当の人となり—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.05,0:52:51.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“良い特質も \N 進歩の必要な特質も—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.79,0:52:55.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,“両方見れるようエホバに\N 助けを求めるんだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.79,0:53:00.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そして 彼女に会ったとき\N 行動を観察すること”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.89,0:53:06.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,“友達や両親 会衆の成員に\N どのように接しているだろうか？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.03,0:53:11.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それは 将来ジミンがおまえに\N どのように接するかを示すものなんだ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.54,0:53:14.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも彼女の事だけではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.14,0:53:18.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 5:25を読むように\N言われました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.61,0:53:22.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,“夫たちよ 妻を愛し続けなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.32,0:53:24.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,“キリストが会衆を愛し—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.15,0:53:28.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そのためにご自分を引き渡されたのと\N 同じようにです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.62,0:53:33.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,父は“このような夫になる準備が\Nできている？”と尋ね—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.49,0:53:36.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,“できていると思うよ”と\N言ってくれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.60,0:53:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 本当のことを\N知っているのは自分だけです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.61,0:53:51.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから 貯金して\N何度も会いに行きました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.11,0:53:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間をかけ わたしたち二人の\N霊的な人となりを知りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.48,0:54:59.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは完璧ではありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.71,0:55:03.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバに目を向け続けるなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.65,0:55:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いにとって完璧になれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.30,0:55:20.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,決定する前に互いをより良く知る方法が\Nあることがわかりましたか? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.23,0:55:24.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,離れてはいても\N霊的な事柄を定期的に話し合い—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.27,0:55:26.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼できる大人に付き添ってもらい—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.77,0:55:30.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,訪問したり 集会や宣教に\N参加したりするなど—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.24,0:55:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚に備える多くの方法があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.25,0:55:37.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,大都市での証言活動に\N参加している夫婦の映像は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.88,0:55:42.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,この証言方法がいかに\N効果的であるかをよく示しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.52,0:55:46.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,米国カリフォルニア州\Nサンフランシスコからの報告によると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.79,0:55:52.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,伝道者たちは2013年から\N大都市での特別な奉仕に参加しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.47,0:55:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟たちは多くの言語グループを助け\N聖書研究を始め 弟子を作っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.42,0:56:18.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,カートを引いていると\N周りの人々に注目されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.59,0:56:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,移動中でも自分がエホバから\N遣わされていることを実感できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を何回も開いて\N話し合えるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.13,0:56:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,心の正直な人たちは聖書の教えを\N本当に知りたいと思っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.01,0:56:42.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書などについて話し合うことが\N難しいところで生活している人にも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.32,0:56:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは\N音信が伝わるようにされます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.55,0:56:49.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,大都市での奉仕に\N参加すると—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.49,0:56:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに引き寄せられるよう\N人々を助けられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.83,0:57:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何千人もの人たちが\N毎日カートの前を通るんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.67,0:57:07.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎週40もの言語で\N配布できますが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.61,0:57:12.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,何よりも たくさんの人たちと話せ \N多くの研究が取り決められることが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.45,0:57:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にうれしいです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.75,0:57:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは地域社会で\Nよく知られています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.85,0:57:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,とりわけ 不活発になった\Nクリスチャンたちにも一目瞭然です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.29,0:57:29.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは世界中から集まる人たちに\N会えるよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.90,0:57:33.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちをあらゆる中心地に\N割り当てられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.77,0:57:38.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,お会いした人たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.14,0:57:42.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペルー 南アフリカ 日本 \Nドイツ 英国\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.91,0:57:48.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,それにフランスやイタリア \Nカメルーンにコンゴからです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.31,0:57:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いっぱい!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.79,0:57:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ショナ語でのあいさつは\Nこんな感じです... \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.57,0:58:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今のは日本語での証言です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.58,0:58:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは手話の\N“聖書を学んでみませんか？”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.15,0:58:28.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,手話の聖書を見たことがないと\N首を振られたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.32,0:58:31.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,使徒 17:27をお見せしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.62,0:58:35.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,見終わると手話で\N“わたしでも分かった！”と喜ばれ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.33,0:58:38.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これが無料のアプリなの？”\Nと驚かれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.63,0:58:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして すぐにダウンロードされました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.74,0:58:45.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある男性に“議論”したい—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.84,0:58:48.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや“ただ話し合い”たいと\N近づかれました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.94,0:58:51.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当は電車に乗るつもりの方でしたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.91,0:58:55.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,３つも電車をやり過ごし\Nわたしたちとずっと話してました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.98,0:58:59.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ語り合って わたしたちの\N違う面を知ってもらうのも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.89,0:59:01.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当に楽しい経験です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.96,0:59:04.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ずしも配布する必要はありません \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.82,0:59:10.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰り際に“あなたたち夫婦は本当に\N素晴らしい大使です”と言われたんです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.93,0:59:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここで聖書研究が毎日のように始まり \Nそれが世界中に広がっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.21,0:59:23.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,アルフレードに会ったのは\N2014年の記念式前でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.48,0:59:25.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,カートに近づいてきたんです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.51,0:59:29.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,生活は苦しく 悪いこと\Nばかりしていましたので—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.12,0:59:32.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も変えられないと\N感じていたようです \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.02,0:59:34.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなに大きな問題を\N抱えていても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.45,0:59:37.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバにとって大きすぎる\N問題はないことを話し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.79,0:59:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書研究を再開するよう\N励ましました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.83,0:59:46.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,“さあ 来るがよい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.30,0:59:50.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしたちの間で事を正そう”と\Nエホバは言われる\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.47,0:59:53.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,“たとえあなた方の罪が\N緋のようであっても—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.44,0:59:56.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それはまさに雪のように白くされる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.08,1:00:02.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが人を許してくださる時は\N完全にお許しになります \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.32,1:00:08.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしはバプテスマを受け\Nその月から補助開拓奉仕を始めました \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.96,1:00:13.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの証人の一人でいられることは\N本当に特権です\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.53,1:00:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界中に仲間がいるんです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.53,1:00:23.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,大都市での特別な証言活動にかかる\N費用や時間が心配でしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.80,1:00:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それともどうしたらいいのか分からず\N慣れてないのでためらいますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.08,1:00:32.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなに心配しないでください\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.01,1:00:35.52,Default2,,0,0,0,, エホバからの割り当てです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.52,1:00:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,機会を逃さず 手放さないで下さい\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.47,1:01:06.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,大都市での証言にサンフランシスコで\N参加している兄弟姉妹たちは—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.05,1:01:09.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎月5000冊以上の\N出版物を配布し—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.48,1:01:13.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,平均185件の聖書研究を\N取り決めています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.82,1:01:19.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,地元当局は金門橋で文書カートを\N置くことに 初め懸念しましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.16,1:01:25.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,今では兄弟たちが聖書の音信を携えて\Nそこにいることに感謝を述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.16,1:01:26.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこでは—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.07,1:01:29.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それでも生きていける 3つの理由”\Nと題する—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.64,1:01:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,2014年4月号の「目ざめよ！」誌を\Nいつも準備しておくよう依頼されていました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.54,1:01:38.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある時 警官が近づいてきて\Nこう言いました—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.81,1:01:41.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,“この雑誌には力がある”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.01,1:01:46.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その警官は橋から飛び降りよう思っていた\N若い女性を助けたばかりでした\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.59,1:01:51.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,警官たちが近づいたとき彼女は手に\Nその「目ざめよ！」誌を持っており—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.22,1:01:53.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,飛び降りないことにしたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:57.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,この体制下での生活は\N誰にとっても困難ですが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.20,1:02:02.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは証言活動によって\N人々を慰め 命の創造者を知って—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.77,1:02:06.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方に感謝するよう\N助けているのです\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.24,1:02:09.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを知る期間が\N長ければ長いほど—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.01,1:02:12.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,その忠節な行ないに感謝する理由が\N多くなります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.65,1:02:15.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして今月の\Nミュージックビデオのように—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.38,1:02:18.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの感謝を歌いたいと\N思うことでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.38,1:02:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,タイトルは\N“「ありがとう」をあなたへ”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.55,1:02:51.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,青い空\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.08,1:02:56.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,探すけど\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.69,1:03:02.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,曇る窓に\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.43,1:03:08.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,陽は射さない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.13,1:03:13.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,戻せない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.97,1:03:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時間〈とき〉想い\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.31,1:03:25.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,うつむく心\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.22,1:03:30.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,そそぎだす\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.82,1:03:36.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,その手 つかんで\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.50,1:03:41.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう迷わない\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.63,1:03:47.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,顔あげて 踏み出せる\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.51,1:03:50.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,この足で\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.31,1:03:56.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが いるから\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.05,1:04:01.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,歩きつかれ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.49,1:04:07.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,凍えそうでも\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.16,1:04:13.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの右手は\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.23,1:04:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あたたかい\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.95,1:04:38.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛に 包まれ\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.22,1:04:43.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,生きてゆける\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.90,1:04:49.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの“ありがとう”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.80,1:04:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,届きますように\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.84,1:05:03.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオの中には\N経済的な圧力に面している家族や—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.05,1:05:07.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康の衰えと向き合っている\N年配のご夫婦が登場しました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.69,1:05:09.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 4:6には—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.42,1:05:12.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,“請願を神に知っていただくように”\Nとあります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.99,1:05:16.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安の原因となる\Nどんな問題に関してもそうできます\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.86,1:05:20.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,忍耐できるよう聖霊を\Nエホバに請願するだけでなく—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.57,1:05:22.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに感謝をささげ—　\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.47,1:05:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“その忠節な者たちを捨てられない”\Nことを確信しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.57,1:05:30.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,マレンフォント兄弟姉妹が\N出演してくださったことに—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.41,1:05:32.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,重ねて感謝します\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.31,1:05:35.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほぼ60年にわたる全時間奉仕で—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.31,1:05:38.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,マレンフォント兄弟姉妹は\N多くの経験をされました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.88,1:05:42.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで今月の後半の\NJW Broadcastingで—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.49,1:05:46.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,インタビューの続編を\Nお届けしたいと思います\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.03,1:05:51.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に美しい神権的な音楽を\N録音するオーケストラの舞台裏を—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.23,1:05:54.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別にのぞいてみることにしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.57,1:06:00.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,2015年12月 16ヵ国から来た\N75人の音楽家が—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.07,1:06:04.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク州パタソンにある\Nスタジオに5日間集結しました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.51,1:06:08.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,15人の技術者と共に\N22曲が録音されました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.78,1:06:11.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中には美しく編曲された—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.75,1:06:15.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,147番“特別な所有物”があります\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.55,1:06:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今年の記念式で歌われました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.77,1:06:29.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーケストラの皆さんが—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.44,1:06:32.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんにクリスチャン愛を送っています\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.37,1:06:36.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ神を喜んで賛美できる\N音楽を備えてくれた—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.18,1:06:39.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,オーケストラと統治体に感謝します\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.91,1:06:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のプログラムを\N共に楽しめました\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.05,1:06:45.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニューヨーク市ブルックリンから\NJW Broadcastingでした\N
